Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the second innings of the Test! The players have made their way out in the middle. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee will open the batting for South Africa. James Anderson will begin with the ball. Four slips and a gully in place. Let's go!
... SECOND INNINGS ...

Right then! The pitch is still assisting the bowlers, and with the likes of James Anderson and Stuart Broad in England's bowling attack, batting is going to be a challenge for the Proteas. Can they put on a strong batting show here? We will find out. Stick around for the second innings of this test.

It's been disheartening for England. They had no answers to the disciplined bowling displayed by the visitors and have been dismissed for a low score. After being 6 down on Day 1, Ollie Pope and Stuart Broad resumed their batting. They did play a few strokes but they both perished soon. Jack Leach added another few runs and took England to a score of 165. Ollie Pope was the highest run-getter for them, he scored a solid 73. Had he had some support from the other end, England could have got over the 200-mark.

It's been a morning that has belonged to Kagiso Rabada! He grabs a five-wicket haul at the home of cricket and leads his team off the field. An impressive bowling performance comes to an end! Dean Elgar's decision to bowl first has paid heavy dividends here. All the bowlers have used the conditions perfectly and have bundled England out for 165. South African bowlers were brilliant on Day 1 and they did not let the advantage slip this morning. They have taken 4 wickets with just 49 added to the overnight score. Kagiso Rabada has been the pick of the bowlers, he ended up grabbing a five-fer, while Anrich Nortje took 3 wickets and Marco Jansen ended with 2.

OUT! LBW! Kagiso Rabada ends with a five-wicket haul! A much-needed reward for his hard work. He was brilliant with the ball on Day 1 and bowled his heart out on Day 2 as well and has now rightly got his name on Lord's honours board. Coming to the ball - It lands on a good length, on middle, and seams back in slightly. James Anderson looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a huge appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Rabada roars in delight! James Anderson though takes the DRS. However, there is no bat involved and the Ball Tracking also shows three reds. The original decision will stay and England are all-out for 165!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: A fullish delivery, around off. Potts looks to work it towards the leg side but gets the outside edge. The ball goes in the air and towards the vacant point region. A single taken.
On a length and outside off. Potts pushes at it away from his body again and gets beaten again.
Serves a good length and outside off. Potts plays it inside the line of the ball.
This time an inside edge! Serves it on a good length again, around off. Potts looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Lands on a good length and around off. The ball seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of Potts blade as he looks to defend.
James Anderson is the last man in.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Marco Jansen finally gets his radar right and gets rid of Leach here. This is a fullish delivery, on off. Leach goes for an expansive drive without much foot movement. The ball swings into him a bit and knocks over the off pole. Nine wickets down now and South Africa would be looking to wrap this innings quickly now.
Commentary.Howout: b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Loses his radar against the left-hander again! Back of a length and it is down the leg side. Leach leaves it alone.
Fuller and around off. Potts leans forward and drives it to covers for a single.
A fullish delivery and it is swinging into middle. Potts blocks it off the front foot.
Overcompensates this time and bowls it full, on middle and leg. Leach clips it through mid-wicket. The batters run three.
Short and wide outside off. Leach looks to cut it but misses. Jansen needs to be closer to the off pole.
Back of a length, on off. Potts blocks it out this time.
Another play and miss! A good length delivery and outside off. Potts tries to push it away but misses.
On a good length and outside off. Potts goes for an ambitious drive but misses,
Fullish delivery and outside off. Potts leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around leg. Potts looks to clip it but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Beaten all ends up! Rabada bowls it in that channel, outside off. Pott tries to work it towards the leg side but ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Tad shorter again and around off. Leach plays inside the line of the ball.
FOUR! Nicely played! Back of a length and around off. Leach rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Swing and a miss! Short and wide outside off. Leach throws his bat at it but misses.
Back of a length and outside off. Leach looks to guide it behind square on the off side but misses.
Back of a length, on off. Leach blocks it out.
FOUR! Slashes and slashes hard for a boundary! Short and outside off. Leach cuts and gets a thick outside edge as the ball runs away through the gully region for a boundary.
Marco Jansen (6-1-18-1) comes into the attack. He replaces Anrich Nortje.
Goes for a wild swing this time but misses. Lands on a good length again and it is outside off. Potts swings across the line but misses.
Almost an action replay of the last delivery, maybe tad fuller. It is on a good length and around off again. Seams away and beats the outside edge of Pott's blade as he looks to defend.
Beats him again! Just short of good length and around off. The ball pitches and seams away a bit. Potts looks to defend it off the back foot but misses.
Serves a fullish delivery, outside off. Potts goes for a drive but does so without much foot movement and gets beaten.
Angles it into middle and leg. Potts works it bit uppishly but in the gap through mid-wicket for a couple.
Serves a good length delivery and it is outside off. Pott defends it inside the line of the ball.
Well bowled! Much fuller this time, outside off. Jack Leach leans to drive this one but he misses.

FOUR! Streaky boundary! On a length, outside off. Jack Leach lunges forward to drive this one with an angled bat, but the ball goes off the outer half past the diving fielder at gully. It rolls away towards third man for a boundary.
This one nips back in, around middle and leg. Jack Leach misses his flick and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
Beaten again! Back of a length, outside off. Jack Leach stays in his crease and looks to push this away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Shortish ball, outside off again. Jack Leach dabs it towards point. He wanted a single there but is sent back by Matthew Potts. Good call from him.
Beaten! Tad shorter, outside off. Jack Leach looks to block this one but he misses.
Bye! A length ball, nipping back in. Jack Leach leaves it alone. A little fumble by Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps, allows the batters to steal in a bye.
Jack Leach walks out to the middle now.

OUT! TAKEN! Kagiso Rabada gets his fourth wicket and South Africa have their eighth! Smart bowling from Kagiso Rabada! Very full ball on this occasion, wide of off. Stuart Broad makes room and stretches to reach the ball. He opens the face of the bat and ends up chipping it towards point. Dean Elgar there takes a good low catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Dean Elgar b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Good-length delivery, on the pads. Stuart Broad flicks it aerially towards mid-wicket. Two taken.
Big swing and a miss from Stuart Broad! Tad shorter now, outside off. Stuart Broad makes room and looks to hoick this over mid-wicket but he fails to get any bat on it.
An in-swinger this time, a length ball, down leg. Stuart Broad backs away and looks to flicks this away but he misses and gets rapped high on his thigh pad.
Play and a miss! A length ball, swinging away, wide of off. Stuart Broad looks to drive it away but he fails to get any bat on that.
A fuller one, wide of off. Matthew Potts gets down on his knee and drives it over point. Two taken. Matthew Potts is off the mark!
Back of a length, around off. Matthew Potts sways away from that one.
Swinging away, outside off, on a length. Matthew Potts dabs it towards point.
Swing and a miss! Shorter one, outside off. Matthew Potts looks to slash this one away but he misses.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, around middle. Stuart Broad once again pushes it off the back foot towards long on. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
FOUR! Nicely done! Shorter one, around off. Stuart Broad uses the depth of his crease, clears his front foot, and punches it through cover for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Matthew Potts covers the line of the ball and blocks it out.
Oh, well bowled! On a length, shaping away, outside off. Matthew Potts stays in his crease and looks to block this but the gets beaten on the outside edge.
Shorter one this time, around middle and off. Matthew Potts ducks under it and leaves it alone.
Fuller one, swinging away, around off. Matthew Potts drives it towards mid off.
Matthew Potts is the next batter in.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Kagiso Rabada has his man! Sarel Erwee can breathe a sigh of relief. His drop catch did not prove to be costly. A fuller one, outside off, not much movement there. Ollie Pope strides forward and goes for the drive once again. This time the ball goes off the inside edge and back onto the stumps. South Africa have got their seventh wicket. Ollie Pope walks off to a round of applause. His fine knock comes to an end.
Commentary.Howout: b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope defends it out.

FOUR! Edgy runs! Too short on this occasion, around off. Stuart Broad looks to pull this one but he manages to only get a slight top edge over the keeper. The ball runs away towards third man for a boundary.
Much fuller on this occasion, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it towards cover. Only a single.
This one swings away, around off, on a length. Ollie Pope taps it towards cover-point.
Swinging down leg, a length ball. Ollie Pope leaves it alone. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and makes a good stop.
Another length delivery, angling in, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope works it away through mid-wicket. Lungi Ngidi chases the ball and keeps it down to two runs.
On a good length, nipping back in sharply, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope looks to flick this but he misses and gets rapped on high on his pads.
Lovely ball! A yorker-length delivery, swinging down leg. Stuart Broad backs away and fails to dig this one out.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short now, shaping it away, outside off. Stuart Broad stays in his crease and looks to push this away on the off side but he fails to get any bat on it.
Stuart Broad takes the aerial route now! Pitched-up delivery, outside off. Stuart Broad lifts this one over cover. Two taken.
Swinging into the left-hander, full again, around off. Stuart Broad drives and finds the fielder at mid off.
Wide of off this time, fuller in length. Ollie Pope presses forward and drives this one away from his body and towards deep point. Only a single.
Angling in, fuller one and around middle and leg. Ollie Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Another play and a miss! Shorter one, wide of off. Stuart Broad looks to cut this away but he misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Stuart Broad lets that go through to the keeper.
Swing and a miss! Anrich Nortje continues to trouble Broad with the short ball, the line is outside off again. Stuart Broad looks to push this one away but he misses.
Anrich Nortje drops it short again, outside off, at 146 clicks. Stuart Broad leaves it alone.
Oh, well bowled! Another shorter one, outside off, swinging away. Stuart Broad gets beaten on the outside edge while trying to block this one.
Anrich Nortje begins with a shorter one from 'round the wicket, outside off, swinging away. Stuart Broad leaves it alone.
Anrich Nortje to start from the other end.

DROPPED! Oh, dear! A big chance for South Africa goes down! A length ball, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope leans to block this one but the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Sarel Erwee there gets his hands to the ball, he juggles it two times, and eventually puts it down. Kagiso Rabada was already celebrating there, but he now stands in disbelief.
Another full ball, outside off, swinging away. Ollie Pope drives it away from his body to the fielder at mid off.
Pitches it up now, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and drives it to the fielder at cover.
FOUR! First boundary of the morning! Shorter ball now, down leg. Ollie Pope pulls it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Fuller now, around off. Ollie Pope drives it past mid off. Two taken. We are underway on Day 2!
Kagiso Rabada begins with a length ball, swinging in, around off. Ollie Pope pushes it towards cover. He wanted a single there but is sent back by his partner.

We are moments away from the start of Day 2! The South African players have made their way out to the middle. Ollie Pope and Stuart Broad the two overnight batters for England also walk out to the middle now. The sun is shining bright and conditions are perfect for some quality Test cricket today. Kagiso Rabada to start the proceedings with the ball. Here we go...
To give you a bit of a weather update, it's not raining in London for now, the conditions are cloudy though. But let's be optimistic here and hope for no rain and only cricket on Day 2.

England were absolutely bamboozled by the South African bowlers. Ollie Pope was the only batter who found some sort of rhythm. He along with Ben Stokes put on a 45-run stand which was the only promising partnership for England. Stokes did perish after playing a few fine strokes but Pope is still standing tall at the crease. He is unbeaten on 61 and will try to build a partnership along with Stuart Broad at the other end and regain some sort of control.

South Africa put on a clinical performance with the ball. All the bowlers justified the skipper's decision to bowl first. They grabbed 6 wickets in the 32 overs they bowled. Anrich Nortje took 3 wickets, while Kagiso Rabada took 2. They will be aiming to continue their good show with the ball and bundle out England as soon as possible.

Hello and welcome back folks! It’s time for Day 2 of this first Test between South Africa and England to get underway. We witnessed a curtailed Day 1 in which only 32 overs were bowed and it’s South Africa that are certainly on top of proceedings. They took 6 wickets on Day 1 and put England under the pump early. With the conditions being overcast and the pitch assisting the bowler's things are only going to be tough for England.

Right then, that concludes our proceedings for Day 1. The action was quite engrossing till it lasted and let’s hope that rain stays away on Day 2. The first ball of Day 2 will be bowled at 3.30 pm IST (10 am GMT). Our build-up though begins a lot earlier. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

UPDATE - 9.07 pm IST (3.37 pm GMT) - DAY 1 HAS BEEN CALLED OFF! It's been raining continuously for over two hours now and the officials have decided no play will be possible. We witnessed only 32 overs on Day 1 and it's South Africa that have dominated proceedings. The visitors have demolished the English batting line-up and find themselves sitting in the driving seat. Dean Elgar's decision to bowl first has certainly paid heavy dividends as they have taken 6 wickets in the span of 32 overs. Anrich Nortje has grabbed three wickets for them, while Kagiso Rabada has taken two. For England, it's been disappointing. Ollie Pope was the only bright star in an otherwise dark day for England. Ben Stokes did play some fine strokes but he could not carry on and was sent back to the hut at the stroke of Lunch. Ollie Pope notched up his half-ton and will be hoping to continue the same way with little support from the other end.

UPDATE - 8.51 pm IST (3.21 pm GMT) - Unfortunately, it is still raining at Lord's! Looks like our not-so-beloved friend, RAIN has decided to have a long stay in the home of cricket. You can't blame rain though, the ground has a rich history, and everyone is bound to get attracted to it.

While we continue to wait here for the game to resume, there is plenty of cricket action going around. Afghanistan and Ireland are battling it out in the fifth and final T20I of the series. The series is firmly poised at 2-2 and the winner of the final game will secure the series. Afghanistan are currently reeling at 33 for 3 at the end of 6 overs. In the Women's Hundred Competition, Oval Invincibles Women and Trent Rockets Women are up against each other at Trent Bridge. So, switch tabs and enjoy the action from these games, but do not go too far away as we will have an update about this game very soon.

As rain continues to pour here at the home of cricket, let’s just take some time to give our regards to Kevin O’Brien who retired from International cricket on the 16th of August, 2022. His biggest moment in the sun came when he became an overnight sensation after smashing a fantastic century against England in the 2011 World Cup. Also, the man is a legend of Irish cricket! He would be forever remembered as one of the players who played a key role in bringing Ireland cricket on a cricketing map. We wish him all the best in his future endeavors.
UPDATE - 7.44 pm IST (2.14 pm GMT) - As expected! Our waiting game continues folks. The rain continues to pour down and with that early Tea has been taken.

UPDATE - 7.25 pm IST (1.55 pm GMT) - Here is one life lesson for all of us. NEVER DOUBT THE KNOWLEDGE AND WISDOM OF A LOCAL EXPERIENCED PERSON! It has started to rain again and quite heavily too. Things are looking quite bleak at the moment and looks like we are in for a long delay.

UPDATE - 7.10 pm IST (1.40 pm GMT) - We have some bitter-sweet news folks! The news coming out from the middle is that the rain has eased out but the covers are still on. It is probably because the groundstaff with their local knowledge are expecting more rain to arrive soon. Let's hope they are proved wrong this time!

While we continue waiting for the game to resume, let's talk about the small passage of play we witnessed in the second session. South Africa came in and continued to trouble the batters with their disciplined bowling and they were rewarded with the wicket of Ben Foakes. Anrich Nortje was the bowler who got rid of him. He grabbed his third wicket and helped South Africa get their sixth. Ben Foakes was the last recognized batter for England, they are into the bowlers now, with Ollie Pope still at the crease. It's only going to get tougher for the home side.

UPDATE - 6.39 pm IST (1.09 pm GMT) - Rain stops play! Uh-oh! It has started to drizzle and the players are walking off the field and the covers have been brought on. It's not heavy for now, but the forecast for rest of the day is not quite promising. But let's hope for the best.

Here we go...bouncer to Broad now! It is quite well directed, angling into the body from 'round the wicket. Broad looks to duck under it but gets hit on his shoulders. The ball rolls towards the off side.
Lands on a length and outside off. Broad leaves it alone.
Stuart Broad makes his way out to the middle.

OUT! BOWLED! Anrich Nortje strikes again and England lose their sixth wicket now! Anrich Nortje with a pacy length delivery, around off. Foakes looks to defend it from his crease but does so away from his body. The ball catches the inside edge of his blade and knocks over the stumps. England continue to lose wickets and with Anrich Nortje bowling over 90 mph regularly in these gloomy conditions, it is only going to get tougher for English batters from hereon.
Commentary.Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Pulls his length back, on middle. Foakes looks to work it towards the leg side but gets hit high on the pads and the ball rolls towards the off side.
Goes fuller on middle this time. Foakes works it right of the mid on fielder.
Serves it on a length, around off. Foakes blocks it out solidly towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Pope defends it towards point and sends back his partner who was looking for a run.
Rabada bowls this just short of good length, outside off. Pope decides to leave it alone again. Nice carry to the keeper.
A tad shorter again, outside off. Pope leaves it alone.
Rabada bangs it short on middle. Pope pulls it to deep backward square leg. Ngidi loses his balance as he stops this ball and the batters take two.
Lands on a length, around off. Pope guides it towards the gully fielder.
Lands on a good length, around off. The ball seams away a bit and Pope defends it off the outside half of his blade towards cover-point.
Another bouncer from Anrich Nortje. Ben Foakes ducks under it and lets it go.
Back of a length, down the leg side. Ben Foakes looks to leave this one but the ball brushes off his thigh pad and goes towards short fine leg. No run taken there.
Anrich Nortje drops it short now, around middle. Ollie Pope miscues his pull shot through square leg for a single.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it towards the fielder at mid off.
Width on offer now, a length ball, at 148 clicks. Ollie Pope looks to cut this away but he misses.
Angling in, a length ball, darting it on the pads. Ben Foakes tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Back of a lenngth, outside off. Ollie Pope stays back and cuts it through point for a brace.
A good-length ball, nipping back in, around off. Ollie Pope gets an inside edge onto his pads while trying to block this one.
Beaten! A beauty by Kagiso Rabada! On a length, outside off, shaping away. Ollie Pope looks to block this but he gets beaten on his outside edge.
Kagiso Rabada pitches this one up, around off. Ollie Pope pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ollie Pope leans to drive but the ball goes off his inner half through mid-wicket for a brace.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Ollie Pope gets on his toes and dabs it towards backward point.
Down the leg side, slightly shorter this time. Ben Foakes looks to flick this one but he misses. A stifled appeal there for caught behind but the umpire is not interested in that one.
Anrich Nortje serves it on a length, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it out.
FOUR! Good timing on that one! A fuller ball, swinging in, around middle and leg, at 147 clicks. Ben Foakes flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. First boundary of the afternoon session.
Good-length delivery, outside off, Ben Foakes blocks it out watchfully.
Another speedy delivery! Outside off, a length ball, tailing back in, at 147 clicks. Ben Foakes dabs it towards point.
Anrich Nortje comes over the wicket, serves a full ball, outside off, swinging in, at 148 clicks. Ben Foakes leaves it alone.
Anrich Nortje to start from the other end.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and drives it firmly through cover-point. Two taken.

Another in-swinger, around middle and leg, a length delivery. Ben Foakes tries to flick this one but he gets a sight inside edge back onto his pads. The ball rolls towards point and the batters cross ends. Ben Foakes is off the mark!
This one nips back in off a short-length delivery, around middle. Ben Foakes looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad.
Another full-length delivery, around middle and off. Ben Foakes defends it out.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ben Foakes blocks it out with the toe-end of his bat.
Quick single to begin proceedings in the second session! A shorter ball, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it towards point and scampers across to the other end.

We are back for the afternoon session! The South African players are out there in the middle. Ollie Pope and Ben Foakes also walk out to the middle now. Kagiso Rabada to start after Lunch. Here we go...
… DAY 1, SESSION 2 …

England though will be disappointed with this batting effort. We all know conditions are tough for the batters in Lord’s, especially in the first two or three days but it is all about applying yourself in the middle. However, except Pope, all other batters struggled to show that application and ended up losing their wickets quickly. The 45-run stand between Stokes and Pope did bring some respite for the English fans for some time but with Stokes departing on the last ball, England now need a special effort from the lower order to put a decent total on the board. Ollie Pope is unbeaten on 51 and can he along with the lower order stage a fightback here? We shall find out in the post-Lunch session. We shall be back at 6.10 pm IST (12.40 pm GMT). Stay tuned...

A fantastic first session for South Africa! They have got five wickets and the wicket of Stokes off the last delivery of this session has put them in a very strong position now. All South African bowlers made full use of friendly bowling conditions and dominated the proceedings as they got good swing and seam throughout the session. Rabada was the man who set the tone and got rid of both the openers in his opening spell. Marco Jansen then bowled brilliantly and showed yet again why he is rated so highly as he outfoxed Joe Root. That crucial breakthrough was followed by the wicket of Jonny Bairstow with Nortje beating him with his rapid bullet and the speedster then ended the session with a big wicket of Ben Stokes.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Anrich Nortje gets rid of the England skipper on the final delivery before Lunch! What a session this has been for the visitors. England are in deep trouble after having lost half their side now. Coming to the delivery - A shorter one from 'round the wicket, outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to push this one away but he gets an outside edge that flies towards third slip. Keegan Petersen, there takes a good catch. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Commentary.Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
EDGED AND FOUR! Outside off, fuller one. Ben Stokes looks to drive this one but he gets a thick outside side over the second slip fielder for a boundary.
Leg bye! On a good length, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope misses his tuck and gets hit on his pads. The ball rolls away towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.

FOUR! Ollie Pope brings up his fifty in style! A fuller one, outside off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and creams his drive through cover for a boundary. A lovely knock from him so far! He will want to convert this into a big one.

EDGED AND DROPPED! A chance goes down. Fuller one, wide of off. Ollie Pope looks to drive this away from his body and he manages to get an outside edge towards third slip. Keegan Petersen dives to his right, sticks his right hand out, but manages to get only his fingertips on the ball. Two taken.
Kagiso Rabada sprays this one down the leg side, on a good length. Ben Stokes lets it go. Kyle Verreynne dives to his right and makes a good stop.
Beaten! Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and tries to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Swing and a miss! Shorter ball, width on offer. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to slash this one away but he fails to get any bat on that.
FOUR! Another fine stroke by Ben Stokes! This is full in length, around off. Ben Stokes drives it uppishly and away from the mid off for a boundary.
Another one wide of off, swinging away, fuller in length. Ben Stokes is not interested in playing that.
A fuller ball, wide of off, shaping away. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around middle and off. Ollie Pope blocks it out off the back foot.
This one angles in, on a good length, on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Anrich Nortje goes over the wicket now, serves a length ball, nips it back in, outside off, at 141 clicks. Ollie Pope does not fiddle with it.
Angling in this time, on a length, around the leg pole. Ben Stokes tucks it toward fine leg and rotates the strike.
On a length this time, around middle and off again. Ben Stokes defends it out watchfully.
Anrich Nortje comes 'round the wicket for the left-hander, serves a fuller ball, around middle and off. Ben Stokes defends it out.
Anrich Nortje is back into the attack. Four overs for 24 runs and a big wicket of Jonny Bairstow for the speedster so far.
A short ball this time, on the body. Ben Stokes pulls it towards square leg for a single.
This one lands on a length, and swings away, outside off. Ben Stokes gets beaten while trying to block this one.
A good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope taps it towards point and takes a single.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short this time, around middle and off. Ollie Pope is happy to let that go. Kyle Verreynne jumps and does well to collect the ball.
Wide of off this time, on a good length. Ollie Pope lets that go through to the keeper.
Tight leave! A length ball, tailing back in sharply, outside off. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
FOUR! Another gorgeous shot from the England skipper! Marco Jansen overcooks this one, around off. Ben Stokes once again, drives it firmly down the ground for a boundary. Good over for England!
Outside off this time, shaping away, on a good length. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Down the leg side, a length delivery. Ben Stokes looks to flick this one but he misses.
FOUR! Glorious! An overpitched delivery, around middle. Ben Stokes shows the full face of the bat and drives it down the ground for a beautiful boundary.
Angling in, on a length, around the thigh pad. Ollie Pope tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Marco Jansen continues to swing the ball back into the right-hander, around middle on a length. Ollie Pope defends it out.
Tad fuller, around middle. Ben Stokes blocks it out watchfully.
Shaping away, wide of off, a fuller one. Ben Stokes shoulds his arms at it.
A length ball now, around off, at 140 clicks. Ben Stokes blocks it out solidly.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short now, around middle. Ollie Pope goes for the pull shot but the ball goes off the inside edge onto his body and rolls towards square leg. A single taken.
Pitches it up again, swinging away, outside off. Ollie Pope presses forward and drives this one away from his body wide of mid off. Two taken.
A fuller ball, outside off. at around 140 clicks. Ollie Pope leans forward to drive this one but he gets undone by the pace.
Kagiso Rabada is back on!
Pulls his length back a bit. However, he drifts down the leg side and Stokes misses it as he tries to clip it away.
A fullish delivery around off. Pope goes across and works it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, on off. Pope defends it towards cover.
Lands on a length, on off. Stokes dabs it towards cover-point for a single.
Back of a length, on leg. Stokes tries to clip it away. However, the ball brushes his thigh pad and goes towards fine leg. Two leg byes taken.

Beaten! This is something we have seen from Stokes all throughout this summer. Jansen bowls it just short of good length, on middle. Stokes dances down the track and looks to heave it towards the leg side but misses.
A fullish delivery that shapes into middle and leg. Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Bowls a fullish delivery, outside off. Stokes drives it firmly to covers. However, Elgar does well to half-stop it and a single is taken.
Angles it into the body. Tad shorter in length as well and Pope works it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Nortje tries something differet and pays the price. Short and wide outside off. Pope jumps and upper-cuts it towards the backward point fence for a boundary.
Lands on a length, on middle. Pope defends it towards the leg side as he takes his one hand off the blade.
Fuller delivery and around off. Pope pushes it off the front foot to mid off.
Jansen continues to bowl full, it is on middle and Stokes blocks it out.
Slight halt in play! There is some movement near the sightscreen which is causing some kind of disturbance.
Full delivery on middle and off again. Pope works it wide of mid on for a single.
This time an inside edge comes to the rescue of the batter! A full delivery that shapes into middle. Pope looks to push it away but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
This is lovely bowling. He has found his line now and is making some good use of the swing he is getting. It is fuller on off, shapes in and Pope drives it off the inside half of his blade.
A fullish delivery on middle. Hint of shape into the batter again. Pope clips it to mid-wicket.

Oh, that's an absolute beauty! Jansen lands on a good length and it is outside off. This time he gets a sharp seam movement into the batter. Pope leans forward to defend it but the ball beats the inside edge of his blade and goes through to the keeper.
Back of a length, on off. Stokes blocks it from his crease this time.
Here we go...Stokes is down the track straightaway! Stokes charges down the track and makes some room as well. Nortje follows him and Stokes ends up blocking it in the end.
Lands on a good length and it is outside off. Stokes leaves it alone.
The skipper of England, Ben Stokes walks out to bat at number 6.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Anrich Nortje gets his radar right and gets a big wicket of Jonny Bairstow! South Africa are right on top now! Anrich Nortje bowls it full. The ball shapes in nicely into middle. Jonny Bairstow looks to drive but misses it completely and the ball shatters the stumps. Both Joe Root and Jonny Bairstow are back in the hut, they were the ones who were at the forefront of English charge earlier in the summer. South Africa showing their might with the ball again!
Commentary.Howout: b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, on middle. Pope works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
This is a fullish delivery that swings back in again. Pope looks to flick it away but misses and the ball hits the pads.
Edged and safe! On a length, shaping away, outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to block this one but he gets an outside edge that does not carry to the fielder at second slip.
Well played by Jonny. This is a fullish delivery that shapes into middle. Jonny Bairstow defends it off the middle of his blade.
Serves a length delivery, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
A fullish delivery, around off. Pope pushes it towards covers for a single.

An appeal for a caught behind but Elgar decides to not take a review. This one lands on a length, on middle. It shapes in again and Pope looks to flick it but misses. The ball brushes his thigh pad and the keeper takes it behind the stumps moving to his left. No damage done in the end.
Goes fuller on middle. Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Nortje angles it on the pads. Pope looks to clip it away. The ball brushes his pads and goes behind square towards the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Pulls his length back, it is outside off and Pope guides it with the angled blade towards point.
Goes fuller on middle. Pope looks to flick it away but gets an inside edge onto his pads this time.
Lands it just short of good length, on middle. Pope looks to nudge it away but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads.
FOUR! Anrich Nortje overcompensates and Pope gets it away for another boundary. Short and wide outside off. Pope stands tall and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! Lovely drive by Pope! Anrich Nortje bowls a half-volley, outside off. Pope leans forward and creams it through cover-point for a boundary.
Lands on a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it towards the off side.

DRINKS! What an engrossing first hour we have witnessed. South Africa are certainly on top of proceedings here. England are in a spot of bother having lost three wickets, including the big fish, Joe Root. They need a nig partnership here. Having said that, the man in form, Jonny Bairstow makes his way out to the middle.

OUT! LBW! Marco Jansen gets a big fish here! Joe Root departs and England lose their third wicket. Jansen bowls it on a fullish length, on middle. It shapes back in nicely and Root looks to flick it away. He misses and the ball hits his pads. There is a big appeal and the umpire raises his finger. However, Root decides to take the DRS, The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracking indicates that it is just clipping the leg pole. It is the umpire's call on wickets hitting. So the original decision stays! Joe Root has to walk back.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Nicely driven! This is a fullish delivery, on off. Pope leans forward and drives it through covers. The batters run three as the fielder cuts it off.
On a length, on middle. Pope defends it towards the leg side.
An appeal for LBW but turned down! Good late in-swing there. The ball lands on a length, on off and shapes back in. Pope looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads but it is going down leg.
Jansen has not got his line right so far! He bowls it full and way down the leg side again. Pope lets it go.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Root pushes it towards backward point.
Serves it on a good length and it is around off. It shapes back in but Root is aware off his off stump and leaves it comfortably.
FOUR! Quality shot from a quality batter! Nortje bowls it short and wide outside off. Root is quick to gauge that length and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
This is an in-swinger! It lands on a length, around off and shapes back in. Root defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length and outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Starts off with a tad shorter length and it is outside off as well. Pope rides the bounce and punches it through cover-point. The batters run three.
Change from the other end as well. Anrich Nortje is introduced into the attack.
Goes fuller and it is down the leg side again. Root looks to flick it but misses as the keeper collects it with a dive.
Lands on a good length and it is outside off. Root pushes at it tentatively and gets beaten.
Tad shorter and around leg. Pope looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits him around his chest and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Goes fuller and it swings in again. However, it drifts down the leg side as Pope misses his flick shot.
Bowls a short delivery but it is way down the leg side. Pope lets it go.
Starts off with a full delivery. It shapes back in from the off stump line. Pope works it to mid-wicket.
First bowling change! Marco Jansen is brought into the attack.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Root leaves it alone.
Ohh, another nasty short delivery! Angling into the body and Root manages to defend it onto the turf as he takes his one hand off the handle.
Lands on a length, on off. Root blocks it out this time.
Oh, what a delivery! Absolute ripper! Rabada lands it short of good length and the ball just takes off sharply after pitching. It is on off. Root hops and manages to defend it towards the off side.
Bangs it short, on middle. Root picks the length quickly and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Rabada is on target again! Lands a fullish delivery, around off. It is not that full to drive and Root defends it off the outside half of his blade towards point.

Leg bye! Another length ball, tailing back in, around his thigh pad. Joe Root looks to clip this one away but he misses. The ball deflects off his thigh pad and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye taken!
Lungi Ngidi fires this one on the pads, a length ball. Joe Root flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
On a good length, around middle and off. Ollie Pope shuffles across and tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ollie Pope pushes it off the front foot towards mid off.
Oh, lovely ball! Tight leave from Ollie Pope! A length ball, nipping back in sharply, around the fourth stump line. Ollie Pope shoulders his arms at it.

A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! Dean Elgar opts for a review. A length ball, swinging in, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope misses his flick and gets hit on his pads. No bat involved there. Ball Tracking indicates that it was missing wickets. The on-field decision stands and South Africa lose a review.
A length ball, down the leg side. Joe Root looks to flick this one but he misses.
The prolific former English skipper, Joe Root walks out to the middle.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This time it's a wicket! Well, this was certainly bound to happen sooner rather than later. Kagiso Rabada gets another wicket and England are now two down. On a length, outside off, not much movement there. Zak Crawley leans to block this one but the ball goes off his outside edge towards second slip. Aiden Markram dives to his left and takes a good low catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Aiden Markram b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Leading edge again but this time it runs away for a boundary! A length ball, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to tuck this towards square leg, but the ball goes off his leading edge away from the fielder at gully for a boundary.
Edged and safe! Slightly short, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to flick this but he gets a leading edge and that falls way short of Kagiso Rabada.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Another three! Back of a length, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope pulls this one in the gap between mid-wicket and mid on. Three taken.
Outside off, on a good length. Zak Crawley looks to block this one but he misses. Well away from his blade though.
Fuller ball, outside off. Ollie Pope walks across and steps out to flick this one through mid-wicket. Three taken!
Well bowled! A few outswingers earlier, and this time Lungi Ngidi nips this one back in, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
A length ball, outside off. Ollie Pope blocks this one watchfully.
Pulls his length back a tad, outside off, on a length. Ollie Pope lifts his bat to leave this one but the ball goes off his toe-end and rolls away towards second slip.
A fuller one, shaping away, wide of off. Ollie Pope is happy to let that go.
Beaten again! Kagiso Rabada is searching for that outside edge. On a length, around the fourth stump line. Zak Crawley looks to block this but get gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
Oh, close! Another length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley looks to defend this one but he bails out in the end.
A length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders his arms at it.
Angling in, fuller length, darting it on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it through the mid-wicket. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters grab three runs.
Fuller one, around middle and off. Ollie Pope blocks it out from within his crease.
Beaten! In the channel outside off, a good-length delivery. Ollie Pope gets beaten on his outside edge while trying to block this one.
Lungi Ngidi serves it on a length, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Beaten! Lovely ball! On a good length, around the fourth stump line. Zak Crawley looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good-length delivery, outside off, swinging away. Zak Crawley is happy to let that go.

Angling in, on a length, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley blocks it towards short leg. The fielder there collects the ball on a bounce and throws it back at the stumps without looking. Zak Crawley was well in though.

FOUR! Lovely shot! First confident shot from Zak Crawley and England! Fuller one, around middle. Zak Crawley presents the full face of the bat and drives it down the ground away from mid on and towards the boundary for four.
A good-length delivery, swinging away, outside off. Zak Crawley lets that go through to the keeper.
In the channel outside the off pole, length delivery. Ollie Pope does not fiddle with that one.
Much fuller now, outside off. Ollie Pope drives it off the front foot towards the fielder at mid off.
Outside off, a length delivery, shaping away. Ollie Pope shoulders his arms at it.
Good-length, sliding down leg. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
Edged and just short! Outside off, on a length. Ollie Pope looks to leave this one but the ball goes off his toe-end and lands just short of Aiden Markram at second slip.
On a length, swinging it down leg. Ollie Pope lets that one go. Kyle Verreynne does well diving to his left to stop the ball.
Back of a length, outside off. Ollie Pope steps down the track and dabs it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tad fuller, outside off, at 134 clicks. Ollie Pope leans forward and blocks it out with the outer half of his bat towards point.
An appeal for LBW, but turned down again and rightly so. This was sliding down leg. A length ball, swing in, around the leg pole. Ollie Pope misses his tuck and gets pinged on his pads.
Pitches it up again, shaping this one away, around off. Ollie Pope lunges forward and blocks it out towards point.
Fuller one again, around middle and off. Zak Crawley pushes it towards mid on and takes a single. He gets off the mark with that.
Angling in, fuller in length, around off. Zak Crawley blocks it out
Ollie Pope walks out at number 3!

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! South Africa have got an early breakthrough! Alex Lees escaped earlier in the over but not this time. Kagiso Rabada has his man! A shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees stays in his crease and looks to push this away, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards the keeper. Kyle Verreynne makes no mistake there.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Another stifled appeal there for LBW, but the umpire says no! An in-swinger now, around the leg pole, on a good length. Alex Lees misses his flick and gets rapped on his pads.
Oh, well bowled! A short ball, around middle and leg. Alex Lees sways away from it at the end.
Shorter ball, outside off and swinging it away. Alex Lees shoulders his arms at it.
Wide of off, swinging it away, on a length. Alex Lees leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! A fuller one, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees leans to drive this one away from his body. But the ball goes off the outside edge and flies over Aiden Markram at second slip, towards third man for a boundary. A tough chance for him, but England have their first boundary.
Much fuller this time, outside off, at 133 clicks, shaping away. Zak Crawley is not tempted with that one. He lets it go. A maiden for Lungi Ngidi!
Wide of off this time, swinging it away, on a good length. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Another out-swinger, outside off and on a length. Zak Crawley does not fiddle with that one.
Sticks to his good length, outside off, shaping away, at 132 clicks. Zak Crawley is happy to let that go.
Another length delivery, swinging away, in the channel outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders his arms at it.
Lungi Ngidi begins with a length ball from over the wicket, outside off, shaping away. Zak Crawley offers no shot.
Lungi Ngidi to share the new ball with Kagiso Rabada.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees lets that go through to the keeper.

A stifled appeal for LBW, turned down by the umpire. Another in-swinger, length ball, around the leg pole. Alex Lees looks to flick this but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. That was sliding down leg.
Oh, good ball! Slightly shorter, nipping back in, around middle and leg. Alex Lees misses his tuck and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
Leg bye! Swinging in, around the leg pole, on a length. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball goes towards square leg off his pads and the batters steal a leg bye.
This one swings in, full and around middle and leg, at 140 clicks. Alex Lees tucks it towards square leg for a single. England and Alex Lees are up and running!
Kagiso Rabada goes over the wicket, serves a fullish delivery, outside off, hint of away movement there. Alex Lees leaves it alone.

Right then, we are all set to begin! South African players are out there in the middle. Alex Lees and Zak Crawley are the openers for England. Alex Lees will take the strike as Kagiso Rabada is ready to start with the ball for South Africa. Here we go...

We are moments away from the start of the game! We are at the home of cricket and conditions are perfect for some quality Test cricket. It is time for the national anthems! We will have South Africa's national anthem first up and it will be followed by the England national anthem.

South Africa (Playing XI) - Dean Elgar (C), Sarel Erwee, Keegan Petersen, Aiden Markram, Rassie van der Dussen, Kyle Verreynne (WK), Marco Jansen, Keshav Maharaj, Kagiso Rabada, Anrich Nortje, Lungi Ngidi.
England (Playing XI) - Alex Lees, Zak Crawley, Ollie Pope, Joe Root, Jonny Bairstow, Ben Stokes (C), Ben Foakes (WK), Stuart Broad, Jack Leach, Matthew Potts, James Anderson.
TOSS - The coin goes up and lands in favour of Dean Elgar. South Africa have elected to BOWL first.

South Africa on the other hand might have a little inexperienced side. Dean Elgar, Keshav Maharaj, and Kagiso Rabada are the only experienced players in their side, the rest are relatively new to playing in English conditions. A significant concern for the Proteas will be the selection of Rabada. He remains doubtful for the first Test after sustaining an injury in the T20I series. However, South Africa will be hoping he is fit and ready for the first game. It will be a massive blow for the visitors if he is not part of the squad. Like their opposition, even South Africa have been exceptional in the longest format. They are yet to lose a Test series in the ongoing WTC cycle. Can they continue their good form? Well, we will know soon. Stay tuned for the toss and other updates.

We are back for England's second innings. The South African players are out there in the middle. Zak Crawley and Alex Lees are the openers for England. Kagiso Rabada to start with the ball. Here we go...
… Third Innings …

It's been a disappointing performance from the English side. They troubled the batters in the beginning with their probing lines and lengths, but they were not rewarded for the same. They did manage to gain control of the game towards the final session of Day 2, but the partnership between Marco Jansen and Keshav Maharaj shifted the momentum back towards the visitors. England though will be frustrated about letting the South Africa tail wag quite a lot in the end. Ben Stokes was the leader of the pack for England, he grabbed wickets in crucial junctures and always kept England in the game. He ended with three wickets. Stuart Broad was the other bowler who took 3, while Matthew Potts grabbed two wickets. It's up to England's batters now! Can they bat long here? We will find out. Stay tuned for England's second innings!

South Africa began their batting with a solid opening stand of 85 runs. Dean Elgar was then dismissed 3 short of his half-ton, his partner, Sarel Erwee though carried on his merry way and started building a strong partnership with Keegan Petersen. Once that stand was broken, South Africa lost wickets in quick succession. Their middle order failed to convert their positive starts. But a counter-attacking partnership of 72 runs between Marco Jansen and Keshav Maharaj stole the show. They took the game away from England and helped their side take a healthy lead. Anrich Nortje and Marco Jansen played a few strokes in the end and guided South Africa to 326 with a lead of 161.

A bit of a frustrating morning for England, but they have finally managed to bundle out South Africa. They can breathe a sigh of relief for now. The visitors though will be mighty pleased with their effort with the bat. They have managed to get a handy lead of 161 and find themselves on top of proceedings.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jonny Bairstow takes the catch at third slip, he almost made a mess of it but shows good reflexes in the end to complete the catch with his left hand. Broad bowls a fullish delivery, outside off. Lungi Ngidi tries to drive it away but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes at a good height and straight to Jonny Bairstow at third slip. However, he fails to pouch it on one go but then takes it with his left hand bending quite low. He looks like a relieved man after taking that catch and rightly so, England are already way behind in this game and they cannot afford to miss these kind of chances. South Africa are all-out on 326!
Commentary.Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: A good-length delivery, outside off. Anrich Nortje throws his bat at it but misses.
Back of a length, on middle. Anrich Nortje looks to guide it towards the off side but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! Stokes kicks the ground in frustration. This is fuller and around off. Anrich Nortje manages to power it through extra-cover for a boundary.
FOUR! This is turning out to be a very handy knock from Anrich Nortje. Back of a length, around off. Anrich Nortje stays leg side of the ball and guides it through the gully region for a boundary.
On the shorter side, angling into pads. Nortje looks to works it towards the leg side but misses again. The ball hits him high on the pads.
Swinging in late and drifting on the pads. Nortje looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards the off side.
Goes fuller and down the leg side. Lungi Ngidi looks to clip it but misses.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Lungi Ngidi plays it inside the line of the ball as the ball shapes away late.
Bangs it short now, around leg. Lungi Ngidi ducks under it.
This is also on a length and outside off. Lungi Ngidi makes an easy leave.
On a length and outside off. Lungi Ngidi leaves it.
Lungi Ngidi is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is what happens when you pitch the ball up with the new ball. England took some time to release it but Broad finally gets his length right and takes an important wicket of Marco Jansen. A brilliant knock from the young man though and he deserved to get his fifty but that's how the game works and he walks back to a standing ovation here. This is a fullish delivery, outside off. Not that full to go for a big booming drive but Jansen does and gets an outside edge of his blade. The ball goes straight into the hands of Zak Crawley at second slip and South Africa are nine down now.
Commentary.Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary.Commentary: A nasty bouncer this time but it is really well played by Nortje! A short delivery angling into off. Nortje rides the bounce and blocks it towards the off side as he takes his one hand off the handle.
Keeps it short and around off. Nortje leaves it alone.
On a length, on middle. Nortje is comfortable to defend it. It has been 40 balls since the new ball has been taken but still no signs of James Anderson.
Back of a length and angling into leg. Nortje works it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Very confident shot from Nortje! Goes fuller on off. Nortje shows the full face of his blade and drives it past mid on for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Anrich Nortje blocks it out.
Pulls his length back a bit, around off. Jansen defends it towards the off side. It is quite surprising to see England bowling short even after taking the new ball.
A fuller delivery and it drifts on the pads. Nortje works it to square leg for a single.
Serves a length delivery on off. Nortje tries to defend it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Shorter in length, on off. Jansen pushes it to covers for a single.
Broad with a short delivery, outside off. Nortje makes room and cuts it towards deep extra cover. The ball goes in the air but there is no one there in the deep. Another three added to the score.
Back of a length, on middle. Nortje blocks it off the back foot.
Stuart Broad (17-2-66-1) comes into the attack.
Bowls a short delivery and it is down the leg side. Jansen lets it go.
Goes wide of the crease and angles a length delivery on middle. Nortje works it to fine leg for a single.
Stokes bangs it short, on middle. Nortje ducks under it.
Back of a length, on leg. Jansen looks to work it towards the leg side. However, he misses and the ball rolls towards the leg side off his pads. A leg bye taken.
Lovely good-length delivery, around off. Jansen tries to defend it but the ball seams away a bit and zips past the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on leg. Nortje rides the bounce and works it to backward square leg for a single.
Short delivery and outside off. Anrich Nortje goes for the upper-cut. He, however, ends up hitting it towards deep extra-cover. The batters take three.
Potts bowls it short, around off as well. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone.
A fuller delivery on middle. Jansen works it through mid-wicket for a single.
On the shorter side, on off. Nortje punches it to cover-point for a single.

FOUR! In the air...but just away from Zak Crawley at the third man region. Potts bowls it short and around off. Nortje makes room and throws his bat at it. The ball goes off the outside edge of his blade and in the air towards third man. Crawley runs forward and to his right but fails to reach it and the ball runs away towards the fence.
Serves a length delivery on middle. Jansen works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Outside off, another bouncer from Ben Stokes. Anrich Nortje jumps to block this one but leaves it alone in the end.
Shorter ball, down leg. Anrich Nortje backs away and does well to fend it towards the leg side.
On a length, outside off this time. Marco Jansen leans forward and pushes it towards the fielder at mid off.
Bye! Ben Stokes errs in line again and spills it way down leg. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone. Ben Foakes dives but fails to stop the ball. A bye taken.
Ben Stokes serves a short ball, down leg. Anrich Nortje looks to pull this one but he misses.
Back of a length, around leg. Anrich Nortje makes room and blocks it out watchfully.
A good-length delivery, outside off. This one keeps a bit low and beatsb Jansen as he looks to defend it.
On a length, around off. Jansen blocks it out.
Back of a length, around off. Jansen tries to push it away but misses.
Lands on a length and outside off. Jansen leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Jansen has a poke at it but gets beaten.
Shorter in length, angling into leg. Anrich Nortje works it away to short leg for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Jansen blocks it.
This is shorter in length and around off. Nortje looks to defend but gets the outside edge of his blade as this ball hurries him. The ball goes in the air but over the gully fielder for a single.
On the shorter side again, on off. Anrich Nortje rides the bounce and blocks it out.
A short ball and around off. Anrich Nortje sways away from the line of the ball.
A fullish delivery, around off. Jansen pushes it to covers for a single.
Lands on a length, outside off. Jansen lets it go.
The new ball is due now and England take it immediately. Ben Stokes has decided to have a go with it
Matthew Potts goes 'round the wicket now and serves another short ball. Anrich Nortje ducks and leaves it alone.
Beaten! A shorter ball, outside off. Anrich Nortje looks to have a poke at that one but he misses.
Wide of off this time, a shorter ball. Anrich Nortje leaves it alone.
Another well-directed bumper from Matthew Potts. Anrich Nortje ducks underneath it.
On a length, much straighter this time. Marco Jansen pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Pitches it up this time, outside off. Marco Jansen prods forward and gets beaten while trying to drive this one.
This is a well-directed bumper. Angling into the body and Nortje manages to block it onto the turf nicely in the end.
Bowls a short delivery that is around leg. Anrich Nortje ducks under it.
Bangs it short, around middle. Anrich Nortje ducks under this one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, what a stunning catch from Stuart Broad! A perfect start for England on Day 3! Matthew Potts strikes in his first over of the day and gets rid of Kagiso Rabada. Another short ball, around off. Kagiso Rabada stays in his crease and miscues his pull shot towards mid on. Stuart Broad there, backtracks sticks his right hand up in the air, and takes a terrific catch. That looked like it was going over him for a boundary! Stuart Broad, you beauty!

We are moments away from the start of Day 3! The English players are out there in the middle. Kagiso Rabada and Marco Jansen are the two overnight batters for South Africa. Matthew Potts to start with the ball. Here we go...

We also need to be wary about the weather here and we would like to tell you that as of now, rain is not expected to intervene for the majority of Day 3. You can never be sure of rain in England though and let's hope that it stays away as it did so generously on Day 2.

England, on the other hand, are down but are not completely out of it yet and they would have confidence in the dressing room as they have already pulled off some spectacular heists this summer in Test cricket. Can they script another fightback? A crucial first session coming up…

The term ‘bazball’ is all around English cricketing circles at the moment but South Africa have shown that the old gritty way of playing Test cricket will never go out of fashion. The South African bowling attack was always going to be handy in English conditions and they lived up to their billing with Kagiso Rabada leading the way. The batting unit then showed great determination and application on a tricky pitch to set this game up nicely for them.

Hello and a very warm welcome folks! We are now ready for Day 3 which is fondly called as the ‘moving day’ of a Test match. However, this Test has already moved at a rapid pace despite rain playing spoilsport on Day 1. South Africa have dominated the proceedings so far and now sit with a healthy lead of 124 runs with 3 wickets still in hand. We saw some fight from England in the final session of Day 2 but they need a lot of things to go their way from hereon to win or even draw this one.
… DAY 3, SESSION 1 …

Right then! That concludes our proceedings for Day 2. After a curtailed Day 1, we have witnessed quite an enticing day of cricket. The first ball of Day 3 will be bowled at 3.30 pm IST (10 am GMT). Our build-up though begins a lot earlier. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

South Africa, on the other hand, will be pretty happy with their performance on Day 2. The day started with Rabada taking his 12th five-wicket haul and then South African batters batted quite well to take a sizeable lead here. The openers set the tone with an 85-run stand and though Elgar departed three short of his fifty, his opening partner continued and played a fine knock of 73 runs. The middle-order batters could not build on their starts but a late seventh wicket stand between Maharaj and Jansen has taken them to a very strong position here. Jansen is still batting out there and he will be looking to bat as long as possible, farm the strike as much as he can and take the lead as close to 200 as possible. Looks improbable, but if the lower order can manage to hang around for an hour, that current lead of 124 will swell pretty quickly.

England though have done well in this final session compared to what they had done previously. They have got five wickets in the session and they should thank their skipper, Ben Stokes for that. He took three crucial wickets and kept England alive in this game. Jack Leach also bowled well but England probably missed the trick when they started bowling too many short pitch deliveries to the pair of Maharaj and Jansen when they were new at the crease. England did not add enough runs with the bat early in the day and then struggled to get wickets on the same pitch that South African bowlers got a lot of purchase from. It's been a tough day for the hosts.

Wow! This South African team surely has that fighting spirit and character that one looks for in Test cricket. Just when it seemed that England are finding their way back into this game with four wickets in a pretty quick time after Tea, the pair of Marco Jansen and Maharaj stitched together a stupendous counter-attacking partnership of 72 runs and that has taken them to a lead of 124 at the end of this riveting Day 2 of the first Test match.

Pitches it up again, outside off. Keshav Maharaj drives it towards cover.

Another short ball, down the leg side. Marco Jansen leaves it alone.
Another short one, outside off. Marco Jansen pushes it towards long off. No fielder there, Ben Stokes chases the ball and keeps it to two runs.

Ben Stokes drops it short again, outside off. Marco Jansen stays in his crease and punches it off the back foot through cover. The ball will go towards the boundary, but there is enough time for the batters to pick up four runs.

Much fuller now, outside off. Keshav Maharaj drives it firmly but finds the fielder at mid off.
FOUR! Crunched! Lovely shot from Keshav Maharaj once again. Back of a length, around middle. Keshav Maharaj pulls it powerfully over mid-wicket for a cracking boundary.

Angling in, on a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.

FOUR! Up and over! Another pitched-up delivery, around middle and off. Marco Jansen shimmies down the pitch and tonks it over mid on for a boundary.

Back of a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it off the back foot.
Ohh...that almost went through! An arm ball that pitches on off and comes in with the angle. Jansen looks to defend it but gets the inside edge onto his pads.

Oops! I think I made that judgement a bit too early. Potts bangs it short on middle and Jansen will be very happy as he ducks under it.

Goes fuller on off. Jansen drives it to covers.

On a length and outside off. Keshav Maharaj pushes it right of point for a single.

On a length, on middle. Keshav Maharaj works it to mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Stuart Broad gets his 100th wicket at Lord's! What an achievement this is, tells a lot about the skills and fitness of the guy. He gets to this landmark with a peach of a delivery. Serves it on a good length and around off. Kyle Verreynne is trapped in his crease and pokes at it tentatively. The ball seams away a tad after pitching and catches the outside edge of Kyle Verreynne's blade. The ball goes straight into the hands of Foakes and he takes it comfortably. Six down now South Africa!
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Drinks break. Just when England were looking down and out, their skipper Ben Stokes has produced an inspirational spell. England have managed to take three wickets in this session so far and they would hope to grab some more quickly and limit the lead South Africa get from here. South Africa, on the other hand, need these two to bat long if they want to stretch this lead of 37 towards 100 and beyond that. An interesting passage of play coming up...
