Finds the edge but it is well short of the slip fielder. On a good length and around off. Rassie van der Dussen pushes at it away from his body. However, the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and falls short of the fourth slip fielder. Good thing was that he played it with soft hands.
Drifts on the pads. Erwee clips it towards right of fine leg and the batters run three.
Goes tad fuller and around off. Erwee tries to drive it away but gets an inside half of his blade and the ball goes towards mid on.
Anderson goes wide of the crease and bowls it on a good length and outside off. The ball seams away after pitching and Erwee leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Erwee blocks it off the back foot.
Tad shorter and outside off. Erwee looks to cut it but misses. He needs to be more careful here.
Bowls it very full and fires it on middle. Rassie van der Dussen decides to block it this time.
FOUR! Nicely played! Leach bowls it short and gives away a bit of width as well. Rassie van der Dussen goes deep in his crease and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Bowls it a tad flatter and quicker on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.
This one is tossed up and is around off. Rassie van der Dussen covers his off pole and lets it go.
Pushes it quicker on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.
NO BALL! It is a tossed up delivery, on off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it off the front foot. Leach oversteps here.
Rassie van der Dussen comes to the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jack Leach strikes on his first delivery after Tea! He got some good turn and bowled quite well in those two overs he bowled before Tea and this really is a good decision by Stokes to start with the left-arm spinner along with James Anderson. This is a classic left-arm orthodox spinner's wicket. He flights this one nicely, lands it around off. It turns away a bit after pitching and takes the outside edge of Aiden Markram's blade as he looks to defend. Foakes takes a sharp catch behind the stumps and England have got a big breakthrough just after Tea.
Commentary.Howout: c Ben Foakes b Jack Leach

Commentary.Commentary: Jack Leach will bowl from the other end.
On the shorter side and around off. Erwee dabs it towards backward point.
Jimmy goes wide of the crease and angles it into middle. Erwee works it towards mid-wicket.
Changes his length and bowls it fuller on off. Erwee drives but finds the mid off fielder.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Angles a length delivery, on off from 'round the wicket. Erwee defends it solidly off the front foot.
James Anderson starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee rides the bounce and punches it through cover-point for a couple.

We are back for the final session of the day! The players have made their way out to the middle. Sarel Erwee and Aiden Markram will resume their batting for South Africa. James Anderson will begin with the ball. Let's go!
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

South Africa began the session by scoring runs freely. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee put on a wonderful partnership of 85 runs before the former was dismissed for a well-made 47. Sarel Erwee continued his merry way and put on yet another strong stand with Keegan Petersen this time. England did get rid of Petersen, but they are still struggling to get the wicket of Sarel Erwee, who is standing tall at the crease batting on 60. He along with Aiden Markram will look to put on yet another big stand. A few positives for England is that Jack Leach did get some turn in the two overs that he bowled. We saw him troubling the batters a bit, and he could be the one playing a key role for England. They will be aiming to grab quick wickets in the final session and end the day with smiles on their faces. Can they do so? We will find out. Do join us at 9.00 pm IST (3.30 pm GMT) for the third session of Day 2.

South Africa have scored 131 runs in the second session of Day 2 and just trail by 7 runs. It's safe to say that this session has also belonged to the visitors and they continue to remain on top. They have set a strong platform here and will be looking to take a big lead in the next session.
Bowls a quicker delivery on middle. It is fuller and Aiden Markram works it to mid-wicket. South Africa are 158/2 at Tea on Day 2!

Beaten! What a lovely delivery! This has been a good start from Leach. He tosses this up nicely and pitches it just short of full length, on off. Aiden Markram presses forward to defend but the ball turns away sharply and beats the outside edge of his blade.
This is a bit quicker and close to off again. However, Aiden Markram decides to leave it this time.

FOUR! This is another classy shot from a classy batter! Leach pulls his length back by a bit and it is around off this time. Aiden Markram goes deep in his crease and punches it through cover-point for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on off. Aiden Markram pushes it to covers.
Leach is getting some good turn here. It is pitched around off and the ball turns away sharply as Aiden Markram leaves it.
Lands it on a length, on off. Erwee blocks it solidly from his crease.
A fuller delivery on middle. Aiden Markram flicks it through square leg for a single.
A fullish delivery and nice shap away from the batter again. Aiden Markram looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
FOUR! Aiden Markram plays a glorious cover-drive now! Jimmy serves a half-volley, around off. Aiden Markram leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off. Aiden Markram rides the bounce and dabs it towards point.
Pitches it fuller, on middle. Erwee defends it off the middle of his blade this time.
This is around off again. Erwee leans forward and defends it with the angled blade towards point.
Flaoted up nicely, on off. Erwee blocks it off the front foot.
Sarel Erwee uses his feet as Leach drags his length back a bit. It turns into the batter again and Erwee gets hit high on his pads.
Nice turn for Leach! This one pitches around off and turns back in. Erwee looks to defend but gets beaten. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the impact is outside off.
Tossed up, on off. Erwee blocks it off the front foot.
Time for some spin for the first time in the game! Jack Leach comes into the attack.
A fullish delivery, swinging into middle. Aiden Markram blocks it off the front foot.

Now bowls a variation delivery. It is an inswinger that drifts on middle and leg. Aiden Markram looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits him high on the pads. There is a stifled appeal but nothing serious.
Jimmy is getting good swing here. This is on a length and around off. Aiden Markram is happy to let it go.
Serves another delivery in that channel, outside off. Aiden Markram makes a good leave.
Lands it on a good length and outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Back of a length and around off. Erwee dabs it towards cover-point for a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Aiden Markram does not fiddle with that one.
On a length now, nipping away, outside off. Aiden Markram is happy to let that one go.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Another full ball, wide of off this time. Aiden Markram takes a big stride forward and drives it crisply through cover for a boundary.
Pitches it up again, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee clips it through square leg and takes a single.
Another fuller ball, outside off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, swinging in, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee clips it towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
James Anderson serves it outside off, a length ball again. Aiden Markram offer no shot.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee taps it towards point and takes a single.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Tad fuller now, outside off. Aiden Markram pushes it towards cover-point and rotates the strike.
A length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee dabs it towards point and takes a single.
A JAFFA! What a bowl by James Anderson! It lands on a good length, nips away after pitching, around the fourth stump line. Sarel Erwee gets beaten on the outside edge while trying to block this one.
A good-length ball, outside off. Aiden Markram lets it go. A successful over from Potts comes to an end.
Matthew Potts serves a slightly shorter ball now, around middle. Aiden Markram blocks this one out from within his crease.
Outside off, on a length. Aiden Markram is happy to let that one go.
Another good-length delivery, outside off, swinging away. Aiden Markram opens the face of his bat and dabs it wide of gully for a brace. Aiden Markram is off the mark with that!
A length ball, outside off, swinging away. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Aiden Markram walks out to the middle now.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This time Matthew Potts gets his man! There is that edge he was looking for. A truly deserving wicket and Keegan Petersen has to walk back. A peach by Potts! He took some time to get his radar right but now seems to have found his rhythm back and is really bowling well here. This one is on a length, around the fourth stump line, shaping away. Keegan Petersen leans and looks to push this one away, but the ball goes off the outside edge towards third slip. Jonny Bairstow there, pouches it safely. England have their second wicket!
Commentary.Howout: c Jonny Bairstow b Matthew Potts

Commentary.Commentary: Just a little reminder for all of us. The on-air commentator, Mark Butcher confirms that this is an extended afternoon session and Tea will be taken at 8.40 pm IST (3.10 pm GMT). He further adds that the final session will also be an extended one and irrespective of whether overs are completed or not, the session will continue till 11.30 pm IST (6 pm GMT) and will not be extended further.
A length ball from 'round the wicket, outside off, at 133 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Angling in, on a length, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee works it away towards mid-wicket.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards cover off the front foot.
Swinging away, outside off, a length ball. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
On a good length, darting it on the pads. Sarel Erwee flicks it through square leg for a brace.
Slightly shorter this time, outside off. Sarel Erwee gets an inside edge onto his boot while trying to block this one.
Oh, a beauty by Potts! Still no edge there. He serves it on a good length, and gets it to nip away a tad, outside off. Keegan Petersen is beaten as he tries to block this one out.
Pulls his length back now, tighter line as well, around the fourth stump line. Keegan Petersen is happy to leave it alone.
A fuller one this time, outside off, swings away. Keegan Petersen strides forward and lets it go.
Another length ball, jagging away, wide of off. Keegan Petersen offers no shot once again.
A length ball, outside off, swinging away. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Matthew Potts overpitches this one, around off. Keegan Petersen knocks it past the diving mid on fielder for a brace. With that, the 50-run partnership comes up between these two.
Beaten! A peach by Stuart Broad! A good-length delivery, swinging away, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Angling in, a fuller one, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen nudges it past short leg. Only a single.
Touch fuller this time, outside off again. Keegan Petersen is not interested in playing that.
Outside off, good-length delivery. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.

Mix-up in the middle...but no harm done! A good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays in the crease and dabs it towards cover. Keegan Petersen leaves his crease for a single, but he is sent back by Sarel Erwee mid-way. Stuart Broad chases the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end, but he misses. Ben Stokes who was backing up misses the ball as well. It rolls away and the batters pick three runs at the end.
Fuller and straighter. Keegan Petersen tucks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Matthew Potts drops it short, angling down leg, extra bounce there as well. Sarel Erwee misses his flick.
Width on offer, fuller in length. Sarel Erwee taps it towards point with soft hands.
Pulls his length back now, tails this back in, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen tucks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
FOUR! Gorgeous shot! A half-volley, outside off. Keegan Petersen lunges forward and creams his drive through cover for a beautiful boundary.
Another out-swinger, length ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen dabs it towards cover-point. No run there!
Outside off, shaping away, a length ball. Left alone by Keegan Petersen.
This one nips back in, on a length, around middle. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee pushes it towards cover off the back foot.

FOUR! Sarel Erwee brings up his fifty in style! Another fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leans forward and drives it square of the wicket to the off side. It's been a fine knock so far, he will be hoping to convert this into three figures.
Another fuller ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee prods forward and pushes it towards mid off.
Jagging away again, outside off, fuller ball. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Stuart Broad pitches this one up, swings it away, outside off, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee does not fiddle with that one.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen defends it out watchfully.
Potts pulls his length back a tad, serves it on a length, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen gets a leading edge away from gully while trying to work it towards mid-wicket. Two taken!
Another full-length delivery, maintains the same line outside off, shaping away again. Keegan Petersen strides forward and leaves it alone.
Matthew Potts pitches it up, swings away a tad, outside off. Keegan Petersen shoulders his arms at it.
Yorker-length delivery, outside the off pole. Keegan Petersen does well to dig this one out.
Angling in, a length ball from over the wicket, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee closes the face of his bat and flicks it through mid-wicket. A single!
A good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards square leg and takes a single. He retains the strike!
On a length now, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out from within his crease.
Fuller this time, around off. Sarel Erwee leans forward and drives it square of the wicket on the off side for a brace.
Another back-of-a-length delivery, maintains the same line outside off. Keegan Petersen taps it off the back foot towards cover-point for a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! Stuart Broad drops this one short, outside off. Keegan Petersen stands tall and looks to punch this one to the off side. But the ball goes off the outside edge away from the slip cordon and towards third man for a boundary.
Tight single! A fuller one, shaping away, outside off, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee pushes it wide of mid off and scampers across to the other end.
Pulls his length back, on middle and leg. Erwee tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Goes straighter this time. It is fuller in length too and Erwee works it to mid-wicket.
Tad fuller and around off. Erwee defends it off the front foot to the off side.
On a length and on off. The angle is taking that ball away from the left-hander again but Erwee manages to defend it off the outside half of his blade.
This one is angled across the batter. It lands on a length and outside off. Erwee plays inside the line of the ball and lets it pass. The ball goes off the bounce to the keeper.
Potts goes fuller on off. Erwee leans forward and drives it straight down the ground for a couple as the fielder at mid off cuts it off.

DRINKS! South Africa continue to sit firmly in the driver's seat! They might have lost Dean Elgar, but Keegan Petersen and Sarel Erwee are motoring along nicely. England have got the ball to talk quite a lot but have not been rewarded. They will need to start taking wickets and regain some control before it gets late for them. Also, Matthew Potts comes back to bowl.
On a good length and outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone this time.

This shot shows how much that last delivery left an impact on Keegan Petersen! James Anderson serves it on a good length and outside off. It swings away this time and Keegan Petersen goes for a wild swing across the line. He ends up getting beaten all ends up.

Now, this is the class of James Anderson! After bowling outswingers from the same line and length, he now delivers an inswinger. Keegan Petersen who leaves it is quite surprised to see that ball coming in sharply this time around.
Another outswinger, it is on a good length and outside off. Keegan Petersen lets it go again.
Pulls his length back a bit, it is outside off and Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Beaten! A typical Anderson outswinger. It starts from around off and swings away late to beat the outside edge of Keegan Petersen's blade as he looks to drive it away.
A short delivery and it is down the leg side. Erwee ducks under it.
Just short of good length and it is outside off. Erwee plays it late and behind square towards the off side.
On a good length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and it is angled into the pads. Erwee looks to clip it but misses and the ball brushes his pads on the way before going back to the keeper.
Stokes pulls his length back. It is around off this time and Keegan Petersen pushes it square off the wicket towards the off side for a single.
Goes fuller and down the leg side. Keegan Petersen looks to flick it but misses.
James Anderson changes his angles and angles it on middle and leg from 'round the wicket. It is a length delivery and Sarel Erwee carefully defends it towards the leg side.
Jimmy goes tad fuller this time, on off. Hint of in-swing there but Erwee presents the full face of his blade and drives it back to the bowler.
Serves it on a length again, around off. Erwee is watchful again and blocks it away.
Lands on a length, on off. Erwee is solid in defence this time.
A fullish delivery that is outside off and Erwee leaves it alone.
Shorter in length, on off. Erwee pulls it in front of square and comes back for the second run.

FOUR LEG BYES! Anguish for Ben Stokes! He bowls a big in-swinger this time. It drifts on the pads and Keegan Petersen misses his flick shot. The ball brushes his pads and goes past the diving keeper for a boundary.
Back of a length, on middle. Keegan Petersen works it to mid-wicket.

Ohh...that is a poor shot from Keegan Petersen! Stokes bowls it on a lovely length that is neither too short and neither full enough to drive. Keegan Petersen though goes for a big booming drive but gets beaten as the ball swings late and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Pulls his length back a bit, it is around off and Keegan Petersen makes another leave.
This time an outswinger that pitches, outside off. Keegan Petersen is happy to leave it alone.
Lands on a good length and it is outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.

A big appeal for an LBW but it seems to be pitching outside leg. This is on a length and it is around leg. Sarel Erwee looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the umpire is not interested.
Goes fuller and it is on the pads. Erwee looks to flick it but misses. The ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side.
On the shorter side and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
A  fullish delivery, around off. Erwee leans forward and creams it through covers for a couple.

Goes fuller, on off. Keegan Petersen drives it and initially hesitates to take a single. However, after the ball passes the short cover fielder, he calls for a run and Erwee after initially being late to react to that call runs across and it is an easy single in the end.
A fullish delivery, around off. Keegan Petersen plays it late and guides it through backward point for a couple.
Back of a length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.

FOUR! It's another good delivery but this time it is a boundary for South Africa. A fullish delivery, outside off. Erwee pushes at it. However, he gets a thick outside edge and the ball races through the gully region for a boundary.

Lovely delivery! This one is just short of good length and angled across the left-hander. Sarel Erwee looks to punch it away from his body and gets beaten as the ball zips past the outside edge of his blade.
Another bouncer, this time better line. It is on middle and Erwee ducks under it.
It is shorter in length and down the leg side again. Erwee is happy to let it go.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Erwee looks to clip it away but misses.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This is an inswinger that drifts on the pads. Keegan Petersen leans forward and glances it nicely past square leg for a boundary.
A fullish delivery, angling into middle. Keegan Petersen blocks it out.
Keegan Petersen walks out to bat at number 3.

OUT! BOWLED! Oh, what an unlucky way to get out after playing so well. One of the most unfortunate dismissals you will see in cricket. Dean Elgar is gutted, he was looking so good and South Africa were almost running away with this game but luck shines for England and they get their first breakthrough. This one is tad shorter and angled into leg. Elgar looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his thigh pads and rolls back to the stumps. Elgar tries to stop the ball but is too late as the ball hits the stumps and the bail falls down on the pitch.
Commentary.Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary.Commentary: On the shorter side, around off. Erwee punches it through covers for a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.

FOUR! Another boundary for Dean Elgar and South Africa are moving along nicely here! Stokes with a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. Elgar punches it through backward point and though the ball slows down near the fence, it still has enough wheels to reach the ropes as Pope puts in a big dive to stop it.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Elgar with an easy leave.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tad shorter and it is around off. Elgar rides the bounce and punches it through cover-point for a boundary.
Just short of good length, it is around off and Elgar punches it to covers.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar with a solid block from his crease.
Angling into leg. A length delivery this and Erwee looks to clip it away. The ball hits his thigh pad and goes behind square on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Ben Stokes brings himself into the attack.
A big in-swinger to end the over! However, it starts from way outside off. Swings back in but still wide and Elgar is happy to let it go.
Jimmy goes tad fuller and it is around off. Elgar leans forward and drives it off the outside half of his blade through cover-point for a couple.
Serves a length-delivery, outside off. Elgar leaves it alone nicely.
Angles it into middle and leg. Tad shorter as well and Elgar gets into an awkward position as he tries to defend it. The ball hits him high on the thigh pad.
Lands on a length, on off. Elgar blocks it off the front foot.

Anderson starts his new spell with an absolute cracker of a delivery! He bowls this on a fullish length and just around off. Elgar looks to drive it away but the ball swings away late and beats the outside edge of his blade.
James Anderson is back into the attack.
In the channel outside off, fuller in length. Sarel Erwee lets that go through to the keeper.
Fuller ball, swinging in, down leg. Dean Elgar tucks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
FOUR LEG BYES! More runs for South Africa! Another length ball, down leg. Dean Elgar misses his flick and the ball brushes off his pads and goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Matthew Potts drops it short now, around middle and off. Dean Elgar sways away from that one.
FOUR! Runs are flowing for South Africa at the moment! Full and firing it on the pads. Dean Elgar glances it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Angling across, on a length from 'round the wicket, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, width on offer. Dean Elgar strides forward and drives it through cover. Three taken!

Pulls his length back a tad, around middle. Dean Elgar looks to flick this one but he gets a leading edge towards the slip cordon. Ollie Pope at fourth slip collects the ball on a bounce and scores a direct hit at the striker's end. Dean Elgar was well in!

An absolute ripper from Stuart Broad! This one lands on a length, it swings away after pitching, around the off pole. Dean Elgar looks to block this but he gets beaten as the ball zips past his outside edge.
Another length ball, tighter line this time, around the fifth stump line. Dean Elgar is happy to let it go.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Dean Elgar does not fiddle with that one.
A length ball, swinging away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Pitches it up, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives this one firmly but finds the fielder at mid off. A good over for South Africa!
FOUR! Second boundary in the over! This one is much fuller and on the pads. Sarel Erwee flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Wide of off again, touch short this time. Dean Elgar chops it off the back foot through point. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and width on offer this time, swinging away. Dean Elgar rocks back and slashes it past backward point for a boundary.
Oh, well bowled! Tad slower this time, a length ball, angling in. Dean Elgar gets beaten on his inside edge while trying to block this one.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar is happy to leave that alone.
Much straighter this time, firing it on the pads. Sarel Erwee tucks it towards square leg. No run there!
Good-length delivery, shaping away, wide of off. Sarel Erwee looks to have a poke at it but bails out in the end and leaves it alone.

A length ball from over the wicket, angling down leg. Sarel Erwee misses his flick and the ball brushes off his thigh pad and goes towards the keeper. A stifled appeal there for caught behind but the umpire is not interested.
Good-length delivery, outside off again. Sarel Erwee watches it sail through to the keeper.
Shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Back of a length, swinging away a tad, around middle. Sarel Erwee looks to work it away on the leg side, but the ball goes off the leading edge away from point for a couple of runs.
Beaten! Slightly short now, tighter line, around the fifth stump line. Dean Elgar stays in his crease and looks to block this but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Change of angle now! Matthew Potts goes 'round the wicket and bowls a length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.

Sarel Erwee serves a length ball, around middle and off, extra bounce there as well. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but the ball goes off his inside edge, onto the pads, and towards square leg. A single taken!
Back of a length, outside off again. Sarel Erwee offers no shot to that.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
FOUR! Glorious frim Sarel Erwee! An overpitched delivery, around middle and off. Sarel Erwee presents the full face of the bat and drives it down the ground away from mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! Streaky boundary! Fuller one, wide of off. Dean Elgar prods forward and look tod rive tit away but he manages to get an outside edge away from gully and towards third man for a boundary.
Another out-swinger, tad shorter, outside off. Dean Elgar lets that go through to the keeper.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Angling in now, back of a length, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar looks to flick this one but he misses and gets hit high on his thigh pad.
On a length now, outside off. Dean Elgar defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely done! Fuller in length, darting it on the pads. Dean Elgar uses his wrists and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

Edgy runs! Fuller again, wider this time. Sarel Erwee goes for the drive again, but the ball goes more off the outer half of his bat towards point. The fielder there manages to get a hand on that one. Two taken.
FOUR! Oh, good shot! Full in length, wide of off. Sarel Erwee lunges forward and creams his drives through cover-point for a boundary.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Sarel Erwee does not fiddle with that one.

Beaten! A beauty by Matthew Potts! This one lands on a length, nips back in, around middle and off. Sarel Erwee looks to block this one but he gets beaten on the inside edge. Still some movement there!
Much straighter again, good-length delivery. Sarel Erwee blocks it out off the back foot.
Matthew Potts begins with a length ball from over the wicket, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out.
Fuller one, wide of off. Dean Elgar leans forward and drives it firmly through cover. Two taken!
Tidy start from Broad after Lunch. However, they need a breakthrough quickly, otherwise it can get quite tricky for them.
Pitches this one up, outside off, swinging in again, at 136 clicks. Dean Elgar strides forward and taps it towards the fielder at cover.
Angling it in on this occasion, a length ball, outside off, at 133 clicks. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it.
Touch fuller again, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and pushes it towards cover.
Much fuller this time, outside off, at 133 clicks. Dean Elgar miscues his drive towards the fielder at mid off.

We are back for the afternoon session! The English players are out there in the middle. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee also walk out now to resume their innings. Stuart Broad to start the proceedings with the ball. Here we go...
… DAY 2, SESSION 2 …

The home team, on the other hand, is right on the back foot at the moment. They were below-par with the bat and now their famed new ball pair of Anderson and Broad have failed to provide an early breakthrough. Ollie Pope was the only one who showed some application with the bat for them and once he departed this morning, wickets started falling rapidly. England have shown the ability to fight back in a Test match since Stokes has taken over the leadership role and England fans would hope that they display something similar in this Test match too. Will we see an English fightback? Or will South Africa consolidate their position? We shall find out after Lunch. Join us at 6.10 pm IST (12.40 pm GMT) for the post-Lunch session.

South Africa have bagged yet another session of this Test match! They had some work to do with the ball in the morning and they did it perfectly by grabbing four wickets quickly and folding up England to a below-par score. The openers were then left with a tricky period to survive and they have done well as England bowlers failed to get any breakthrough. All South African bowlers bowled brilliantly but Rabada was the pick as he finished with a five-wicket haul and South Africa are surely showing here why they have been so successful in Test cricket in recent times.
Matthew Potts comes over the wicket now, serves a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee offers no shot. That will be Lunch on Day 2!
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Wide! Fuller in length, wide of off, swinging further away. Sarel Erwee is happy to let that one go. Wide called!
An out-swinger now, wide of off, fuller in length. Sarel Erwee watches it sail through to the keeper.
Swinging in this time, outside off, on a length, at 131 clicks. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 135 clicks. Sarel Erwee defends it out watchfully towards cover.
Back of a length, shaping away, outside off. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
Fuller in length, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it towards cover.
James Anderson pitches it up again, and maintains the same line outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward and defends it out.
Bowls a full-length delivery, angling in, around off. Dean Elgar strides forward and blocks it out towards point.
Slightly shorter on this occasion, swinging away, outside off. Dean Elgar blocks it out off the back foot.
Much fuller this time, around off, at 136 clicks. Dean Elgar leans forward, closes the face of his bat, and blocks it out.
James Anderson serves a good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Lovely delivery! Potts bowls a fullish delivery. It is around off and Erwee tries to drive it away. However, the ball swings away and beats the outside edge of his blade.

FOUR! Potts finds the edge this time but Crawley is late to react at second slip and the ball goes away for a boundary in the end. Back of a length and around off. Bit of swing away from the batter. Elgar tries to punch it away. However, he gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes quite quickly towards Zak Crawley. It is just over him and the English opener gets his hands to the ball but fails to grab it and Elgar gets away with a lucky boundary.

Potts goes fuller and he bowls it around off this time. Erwee shows the full face of his blade and drives it past mid off. The ball though is cut off by the fielder before reaching the ropes and the batters run three.
Back of a length and down the leg side. Erwee leaves it alone.
A fuller delivery on middle. Erwee pushes it to mid on.
Matthew Potts comes into the attack.
Tad shorter and outside off again. Elgar with an easy leave again.
A fuller ball, swinging in, around the leg pole. Dean Elgar misses his flick and gets rapped on his pad.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
On a length, on middle. Elgar defends it towards mid-wicket.
A fullish delivery on middle. Erwee looks to drive but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball goes towards the backward square leg region for a single.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.

Elgar is given out caught behind but he has reviewed it straightaway. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracking also shows that the ball is missing the stumps and the decision will be overturned. This delivery lands on a good length, on off. It comes back in sharply and beats Elgar as he looks to defend. The ball brushes his pads on the way and Foakes takes the catch behind the stumps. The umpire raises his finger after an appeal but it is overturned in the end.
On a length, on off. Elgar blocks it off the front foot.
Goes fuller on middle. Erwee works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Serves it on a good length and it is around off. Erwee leaves it alone as the ball seams away a bit.
This is too wide outside off again. On a length and too easy for Erwee as he leaves it.
Broad just like his new ball partner, bowls a good length delivery. It is outside off and Erwee leaves it alone.
Again it is too wide outside off. Elgar makes an easy leave.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Bowls it tad fuller and angling into middle and leg. Elgar looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the umpire says no..
On a length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.

An absolute ripper this time! Anderson continues to bowl it on a good length, closer to off and this time the ball swings and seams away. Elgar is beaten all ends up as he looks to defend it off the front foot.

Ohh..almost a wicket there! On a good length, around off. Erwee is late on his leave and gets the inside edge of his blade. The ball goes just past the stumps and Foakes half-stops it with a dive to his right. A single taken.
This time an easy leave. It is on a length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Better from Broad! Serves it on a good length but this time it is closer to the off pole. Elgar is in two minds whether to leave it or play. He ends up making a good leave in the end.
On a length, on middle. Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Elgar has loads of patience in his game and is not going to go after this wide deliveries. This one again is on a good length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Serves it on a good length and it around off. Elgar makes a watchful leave again.
On a length and outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Anderson with a fuller delivery on leg again. Erwee clips it to fine leg for a couple.
A fullish delivery, around leg. Erwee tries to flick it away but misses and gets hit on his pads. The fielders appeal but Anderson knew that it was going down leg.
Goes a bit fuller on leg. Erwee clips it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Erwee defends it onto his pitch.
On a good length and outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
This is fuller and down the leg side. Sarel Erwee looks to flick it but misses.
On a length and around off. Erwee pushes it right of cover for a single.

Goes tad fuller and it is angled into off from Broad. Erwee tries to drive but does not keep his bat straight and angles it towards the leg side. The ball goes off the outside half of his blade towards the off side.
Broad serves it on a good length, angling into off. Erwee defends it back to the bowler.
Lands on a good length and outside off. Erwee with a watchful leave.
FOUR! Sarel Erwee is off the mark with a boundary! Broad goes straighter and it is fuller as well. Erwee clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

Inside edge there! Broad serves it on a good length, around off. The ball seams back in and Erwee gets the inside edge onto his pads as he looks to defend. A very optimistic appeal from Broad but no damage done.
Goes tad shorter and it is outside off as well. Elgar is happy and pretty comfortable in his leave.
Lands on a length again, on off. Elgar is solid in defence this time.
Serves it on a good length and it is outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
On a length, on middle. Elgar works it towards mid-wicket.

Jimmy has drifted down the leg side again. He did the same two times in his first over and got away with it and he has got away with this one as well. It is around leg and fuller. Sarel Erwee looks to flick it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes to the right of Foakes. He half-stops it and a leg bye is taken.

Serves it on a good length and around off. Elgar takes his one hand off the handle as he defends it. The ball goes off the outside half of his blade towards fourth slip and the fielder there dives to stop it. There was swing for James Anderson in his first over but not much for Broad in his first over.
Pulls his length back a bit, on middle. Elgar blocks it out.

On a length, on off. Elgar defends it off the outside half of his blade.
FOUR! Glorious shot! First boundary for Elgar and South Africa! Broad overpitches it, on middle. Elgar leans forward and drives it past mid on for a boundary.
Starts off from 'round the wicket and lands it on a length, on off. Elgar with a solid block off the front foot.
Stuart Broad will share the new cherry with James Anderson.
This one pitches around leg and swings further down the leg side. Sarel Erwee looks to flick it but misses and Foakes again with makes a good stop diving to his right.
Tad fuller, on off. Elgar defends it off the front foot towards covers and takes his first run of the game. South Africa are underway as well!
Serves it on a good length, around off. Elgar knows that he is better off leaving these deliveries and he does exactly that.

James Anderson goes tad shorter and comes closer to the off pole. Agan an outswinger and Elgar is happy to leave that alone.
James Anderson with his typical outswinger! It lands on a good length and is outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.

Right then, that concludes our proceedings of this first Test match. It has been a dominant performance by the Proteas and with that, they have grabbed crucial World Test Championship points as well from this historic win. The caravan will now move to Manchester for the second Test. That game is set to take place on Thursday, 25th of August at 3.30 pm IST (10 am GMT). Our build-up though begins a lot earlier. So do join us for the same. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Kagiso Rabada the Player of the Match. He says that is special to contribute to a team win and adds that to do it in Lords’s is pretty special. Tells that he did not even know about the stats, he just tried to follow his process and stick to his strengths, and then the rest took care of itself. Talks about his learnings from the 2017 tour and says that is all about getting the lengths right and adjusting with the Duke ball. He applauds Keshav Maharaj for his performance in this game and says that he has been an outstanding performer for them over the years. Also mentions that his two wickets really helped them. Signs off by saying that he is looking forward to the next game.

Dean Elgar the captain of South Africa says that this is a brilliant effort from the boys and they did not expect the game to finish so quickly. Tells that they wanted to bat long and hard and tells that Anrich Nortje's spell changed the game. Mentions that his decisions come with positive intent and he likes his boys to express themselves. Adds that they played in a South African way, their unique way. Talks about his captaincy and says that it depends on his gut feeling and the move to bring Keshav Maharaj was his gut feeling and then Anrich Nortje bowled with the speed of light. Also credits Sarel Erwee and tells that the partnership between them has been quite good and adds that he is an experienced player and wants his boys to enjoy this win.

Ben Stokes the skipper of England tells that they are disappointed to lose but they cannot drift away from their plans after just one loss. Mentions that they will continue to play the way they are playing and it is just about execution which they did not do well in this game and credits South Africa for the way they played. Adds that all the captains before him have also been criticized for the way the team has played and says that it is a part and parcel of the game. Says that they can’t give excuses about not having red-ball cricket before this game. He credits Ollie Pope for the way he played in testing conditions and sarcastically adds that he wants to win the toss in the next game.

Earlier in the Test, Dean Elgar won the crucial toss and made the perfect decision to bowl first. His bowlers justified his decision to bowl first as they bundled out England for 165. Kagiso Rabada was the one who grabbed a five-wicket haul in the first innings and Ollie Pope scored 73 and was the stand-out player for England. Coming to bat, the openers of South Africa put together 85 runs and set a perfect platform and the right tone for the others. Keshav Maharaj and Marco Jansen then put on a fiery stand of 72 runs and kept South Africa in the driving seat. They eventually ended up getting a lead of 161 runs which did prove enough in the end. Ben Stokes and Stuart Broad were the picks of the bowlers for England.

A tough loss for England! This was the first time, England were batting first under their new head coach and captain, Ben Stokes, and things have certainly not worked for them. They were bundled out for 165 runs in the first innings and 149 in the second. Their bowling too was not up to the mark in this game. None of their batters got going while coming to bat for the second time. They started off well, Zak Crawley and Alex Lees put on an opening stand of 20 runs but they failed to carry on. Zak Crawley was the first one to depart and after that wickets kept falling in a heap. Ben Stokes and Stuart Broad then put on a counter-attacking stand of 55 runs and gave their side a slight glimmer of hope. But Stuart Broad perished soon and then there we no further partnerships created. England were eventually all-out for 149.

It's been a complete team performance from the visitors! They had put England under the pump after the first session and made sure to capitalize on that moment in the second session as well. They have bowled exceptionally well, and have bamboozled the English batting line-up. They grabbed 8 wickets in the second session of the game and sealed a comfortable victory.  Lungi Ngidi was the man to grab the first wicket of the second session, he got rid of Joe Root for a timid score. Anrich Nortje then followed that up with 3 quick wickets and put England under immense pressure. Ben Stokes and Stuart Broad then put on a stand of 55 runs and gave the crowd at Lord's something to cheer about. But that did not last very long as Kagiso Rabada came in and broke the stand between them. Marco Jansen then wrapped things off by grabbing the final two wickets.

South Africa have pulled off an emphatic victory at the home of cricket, Lord's! They have managed to stop the juggernaut of this strong England Test team and have continued to shine in the longest format of the game. Before the game, Dean Elgar did mention, that they are not afraid of the 'Bazball' approach by the English team and he and his side have certainly lived up to what he said. It's been a surreal performance from the visitors, and with this win, they have taken a 1-0 lead in this 3-match Test series.

OUT! BOWLED! That's it! South Africa win! What a performance this has been, a true team effort. They stayed true to their strengths playing old-fashioned cricket with great grit and determination and delivered a solid performance in the end. Coming to the ball - This is very full and swings away late from middle. James Anderson skips down the track and backs away a bit too much. He tried to dig it out but is too late as the ball goes onto shatter the stumps. Marco Jansen is elated and so are other players, they truly deserve this win. South Africa win by an innings and 12 runs!
Commentary.Howout: b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Good late swing for Jansen! This is on a fullish length, on off. James Anderson looks to drive it away but the ball swings away and beats the outside edge of Jimmy's blade.
Another play and a miss! On a good length and outside off. James Anderson drives away from his body but misses.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. James Anderson tries to drive it away but misses.
Good length, outside off. Jack Leach pushes it towards point fielder.
On a length, on off. Leach gets the inside edge onto his pads as he looks to defend it.
NO BALL! Back of a length, on off. Leach dabs it towards point. Another no ball from Rabada.
Back of a length, around off. Leach guides it towwards backward point. Anrich Nortje moves sharply to his right and stops it with a dive.
NO BALL! Rabada oversteps here! Back of a length, around off. James Anderson defends it towards the off side and takes a single. There is a big roar from the crowd.
On a length and down the leg side. James Anderson looks to clip it away but misses.
Beats him first up! Lands it on a good length, around off. It is angled across and the ball zips past the outside edge of Jimmy's blade as he looks to defend.
James Anderson is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Here is the final nail in the coffin! Ben Stokes departs! Rabada bowls it full on middle. Stokes heaves it aerially but does not get enough power behind his shot to clear the fence. it goes flat and towards the deep mid-wicket region where Keshav Maharaj runs to his left and dives to take a good low catch. South Africa are just one wicket away now!

Commentary.Commentary: Jack Leach is the next batter in.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Marco Jansen gets his first wicket of this innings and South Africa inch closer to a historic win here at Lord's! This is full and straight on middle. It shapes back in nicely and Potts goes for a big hit down the ground. He misses and the ball shatters the stumps. Jansen is elated and England sink further.

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, around leg. Potts gets across and looks to work it towards the leg side but misses.
A fullish delivery on middle. Stokes drives it to long on for a single.
Lands it on a length, around leg. Stokes looks to clip it but misses.
Goes fuller on middle. Stokes works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
On a length, on off. Stokes blocks it out.
Good length, attacking the stumps. Matthew Potts plays it towards the mid-wicket region.
Tad shorter on middle again. Stokes clips it to square leg for a single.
On a length, on middle. Potts works it past square leg for a single.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Potts throws his bat at it but misses.
Matthew Potts comes to bat now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kagiso Rabada outfoxes Stuart Broad with a slower delivery and breaks this counter-attacking partnership between Broad and Stokes. This was bound to happen sooner rather than later, Broad was going for everything and Rabada is too good a bowler to let him do that regularly. Back of a length, on off. It is a slower delivery and Broad ends up playing it early. He gets the toe-end of his blade as he looks to loft it away and hits it straight to Dean Elgar at mid off. The skipper takes an easy catch and England are seven down now.

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, on off. Broad heaves it and does not time it properly. However, he ends up getting enough blade to take it over mid on and comes back for the second run.
NO BALL! Back of a length, around off. Stokes guides it to third man for a single. Rabada oversteps here.
Kagiso Rabada (6-2-18-0) comes back to bowl.
Good length, down leg. Stuart Broad makes room and looks to go big again, but he fails to get any connection on that.
Full and on the pads. Stokes works it to fine leg for a single.
A full delivery and down the leg sidde. Broad leaves it. Kyle Verreynne dives to his right and half-stops it. A  bye taken. 50 runs partnership comes up.

FOUR! Runs are flowing for England here! Jansen bangs it short, on middle. It is a very well-directed short delivery and Broad looks to sway away from the line of the ball. He though keeps his angled bat near the shoulder and the ball kisses the blade to go over the keeper for a boundary.
A full delivery on leg. Stokes looks to clip it away but misses. The ball goes off his pads towards the leg side. A leg bye taken.
Goes fuller on leg. Broad skips down the track and works it to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller length, outside off. Stuart Broad cuts it towards point but a good stop by Kagiso Rabada keeps it down to a single.
FOUR! Broad is really enjoying himself here. A full delivery on off. Broad drills it towards the long off fence for a boundary.
Broad contiunes to throw his bat at everything. Broad makes room and Nortje bowls a full delivery, around leg. Broad misses his slog and the ball goes just past the leg stump.
A fullish delivery, around off. Broad backs away and swings hard but misses.
Back of a length, around off. Stokes dabs it towards backward point for a single.

FOUR! Another tough chance goes down! A fuller delivery on off. Stokes hits it hard and straight to Nortje. He gets a good hand to it. However, this catches are always tough on the follow through and the ball deflects off his hand towards the long on fence for a boundary.

EDGED AND FOUR! A fuller one from Marco Jansen, outside off, shaping away. Stuart Broad swings his bat at it and manages to get a thick outside edge. The ball flies over the leaping second slip fielder towards third man for a boundary.
On a length and outside off. Broad throws his bat at it but misses.
Back of a length, on leg. Stokes backing away again tries to clip it. He misses and a leg bye is taken as the ball rolls towards the leg side.
A bouncer on middle. Stokes backs away but ends up only blocking it.
On a length and outside off. Stokes skips down the track and looks to go inside out but misses.
On a length and outside off. Stokes tries to cut it but misses.

In the air..but safe! Broad again shows his stumps and the bowler follows him again, on leg. Broad looks to heave it towards the leg side. However, he gets a huge top edge and the ball goes in the air towards cover-point. Rabada running across to his left dives to catch it but the ball falls away from him. Two taken.
SIX! Broad with a maximum now! Stuart Broad backs away again and Nortje follows him. He bowls it short and Broad hooks it over deep square leg for a maximum.
On the shorter side again, angling into the body. Broad blocks it away awkwardly.
Back of a length, on off. Broad backs away and has a wild swing at it but misses.
FOUR! Two boundaries in a row now! Nortje bowls it short on middle. Broad backs away and slaps it towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
FOUR! Probably this is the only way Broad is going to play against the pacers. It is shorter in length, around off. Broad makes room and cuts it over point for a boundary.
Good length, outside off. Stuart Broad just plays it towards the point region for a single.
This time he connects the sweep! A fuller one, spinning in, around middle. Stuart Broad sweeps it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Turning back in, fuller ball, around middle. Stuart Broad stretches forward to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
Fuller one, around middle and off. Stuart Broad blocks it out.
Tosses it up, full, around off. Stuart Broad blocks it out with the inner half of his bat.

Leg bye! A huge shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! A fuller ball from 'round the wicket, around off. Ben Stokes looks to sweep this one, but he misses and gets hit on his back pad. South Africa though go up for the review. No bat involved there. The Ball Tracking indicates that it was missing the wickets and the impact was the umpires call as well. Not out it is! There was a throw at the non-striker's end, but well away from the stumps. They cross and get a run as well.

Drinks break. What a passage of play this has been for South Africa! They have managed to take four wickets after the Lunch and now are in with a great chance to finish this game off on Day 3 itself. Anrich Nortje after struggling a big initially got his rhythm back and is now bowling with lot of fire and has broken the backbone of the English middle-order in the process. England still have their skipper, Ben Stokes at the crease but with just bowlers to partner him now, things look quite bleak for England.
EDGE! Back-of-a-length delivery, around off. Broad pushes at it away from his body but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes in the air but falls just short of the diving gully fielder.
Shorter ball, around the off pole. Stuart Broad blocks it out towards point.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes dabs it towards the point region. A single taken.
Play and a miss! A length ball, swinging back in, outside off. Ben Stokes stays in his crease and looks to cut this one away but he misses.
A length ball, around middle. Ben Stokes pushes it past mid on for a brace.
Back of a length, on middle at 151 kph. Stokes works it towards short fine leg.
Fuller length, darted on the pads. Stuart Broad defends it comfortably.
Swing and a miss! Loopy ball, outside off, fuller one. Stuart Broad looks to sweeps this one but he misses.

Kyle Verreynne pouches it safely. England are in a spot of bother now.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Anrich Nortje

Commentary.Commentary: Beaten! Lovely ball! Slightly shorter this time, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow looks to push this one away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Cut away! A length ball, little bit of width there outside off. Jonny Bairstow rocks back and slashes it past point for a boundary.
Fuller length. Alex Lees dances down the pitch and hits it straight in the hands of Keshav Maharaj along the ground.
Pitches it up again, around off, tossed up delivery. Alex Lees pushes it back to the bowler.
Spinning in, a fuller ball, around middle. Alex Lees looks to reverse-sweep this one, but the misses. The ball hits his back and goes towards the leg slip fielder.
Tad quicker, around middle, full in length. Jonny Bairstow dances down the pitch and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy ball, full and around off. Jonny Bairstow lunges forward and defends it out.
Tosses it up, fuller one, around off. Alex Lees prods forward to drive this but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on. A single taken.
Good length, on the middle stump line. Jonny Bairstow plays it with straight bat towards the bowler.
Swing and a miss! A fuller one, outside off. Jonny Bairstow leans to drive this one but he misses.
FOUR! Top shot! Short and width on offer this time. Jonny Bairstow rocks back and punches it off the back foot through cover-point for a boundary.
Shorter ball, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow looks to pull this one but he misses and gets hit on his body.
On a length now, around middle and off. Jonny Bairstow closes the face of his bat and tucks it towards fine leg. Two taken.

Anrich Nortje bowls it short, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pulls it in the vacant deep mid-wicket region. Kagiso Rabada runs in from deep square leg to cut that one off. He keeps the ball away from the ropes, but the batters run four runs.
Fuller length, on middle. Alex Lees works it towards the mid-wicket region.

Tosses this one up, bowls it around the off pole, full in length. Jonny Bairstow presses forward and looks to block this but the ball goes off the outside edge away from the first slip fielder. A single taken.
Flighted ball, full and around middle and off. Jonny Bairstow prods forward and blocks it out watchfully.
Floats this one up, delivers it very full this time, around middle. Jonny Bairstow keeps it out.
Another loopy ball, full and around off. Jonny Bairstow leans forward and blocks it out.
Tosses this one up, serves it very full, around middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards mid off.
Short of good length. That ball didn't bounce as much as Lees expected it to be as he misses his pull shot. Gets hit just around the box.
Outside off, on a length, at 145 clicks. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Angling in, shorter ball, around middle and leg. Alex Lees works it away through mid-wicket for a brace.
A good-length delivery now, outside off, at 143 kph. Alex Lees leans forward and blocks it towards point.
Back of a length, outside off, nipping in a tad. Jonny Bairstow taps it off the back foot towards cover for a single.
Anrich Nortje begins with a length ball, darting it on the thigh pad, at 140 clicks. Alex Lees tucks it towards fine leg for a single.
Anrich Nortje is introduced into the attack.
Fuller length, on the middle and leg stump. Jonny Bairstow works it towards short leg. The fielder there is quick to react as he stops it and throws it back to the keeper.
Bowls it tad shorter and gets good turn. The ball drifts on the pads and Lees works it just past the short fine leg fielder for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Lees drives it to covers.
Turning into middle and Lees works it towards mid-wicket with the turn.
Tossed up, around leg. Jonny Bairstow works it towards square leg and gets off the mark.
Tad shorter angling into middle. Lees goes back and punches it to long on for a single.
Short ball, rises off the pitch. Jonny Bairstow manages to keep it down to the turf.
Pulls his length back a bit, outside off at 142 kph. Jonny Bairstow looks to punch it away but does not get any timing in that shot.
Serves a length delivery, on off. Jonny Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
Bowls a yorker, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Ohh...lovely bowling! Ngidi lands it on a length, around off. The ball nips back in sharply and goes just past the off pole as Jonny Bairstow leaves it.
Jonny Bairstow comes to the crease.

OUT! CAUGHT! Joe Root departs! A rare twin failure for the former English skipper. This is a big, big wicket for South Africa! Lungi Ngidi is elated and so are other South African players. South Africa are right on top here. This is a fullish delivery, outside off. Root goes with hard hands for a drive and ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball goes straight into the hands of Aiden Markram at second slip and England lose their most dependable batter.
Commentary.Howout: c Aiden Markram b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller length, attacking the stumps. Alex Lees drives it towards the cover region.
Beaten! Pushes it quicker and it is around off. Lees tries to drive it away but gets beaten.
Root brings out a reverse-sweep now! This is fuller on off. Root kneels and reverse-sweeps it fine through the third man region. They take three. Good running.
Loopy delivery, on off. Root leans forward and blocks it out.
Bowls it fuller on middle. Lees works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Root paddles it towards the fine leg region for a single.
Fuller length, on the stumps. Alex Lees plays it towards the point region.
Lands on a good length again, bit wider outside off and Lees leaves it alone.
Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. Lees makes a careful leave.
Tad shorter in length, around off. Lees defends it onto the turf.
Back of a length, around off. Lees defends it towards the off side and looks for a single but is sent back by his partner.
On a length, on off. Lees pushes it to mid on.
Root advances down the track and Keshav Maharaj drags his length back, on middle. Root ends up padding it away.
Slower through the air, around off. Lees defends it towards the off side and takes a single.
Turning into leg again. Lees works it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Turning into middle. Lees works it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on middle. Lees defends it off the front foot.
This one pitches on middle and turns down the leg side. Lees tries to work it towards the leg side but misses.
That ball was on the pads and Alex Lees just guides it towards the fine leg region for a single.
On the shorter side, around off. Lees tries to pull it but gets the inside edge. The ball goes just past stumps and the keeper makes a good stop diving to his right.
Fuller length, outside off. Lees cuts it towards the point region.
Goes fuller on off. Lees drives it through covers and comes back for the second run.
EDGED AND FOUR! On a good length and outside off. Alex Lees stands tall and looks to punch this away but the ball goes off the outside in the gap between third slip and gully for a boundary.
Serves it on a length, around off. It jags back in and Root defends it towards point for a single.
Bowls it bit quicker on middle. Lees works it towards midwicket.
He is off the mark. This is fuller, on off. Root drives it through covers for a single.
Slower through the air, on middle. Root with a solid front foot defence.
Root uses his feet and drives this full delivery on off to mid off.
Nice flighted delivery, on off. Root blocks it off the front foot.
A flatter delivery turning into middle. Lees stands tall and pushes it to mid on for a single.
Keshav Maharaj (3-0-6-2) will bowl from the other end.
Angles this full delivery on the pads. Lees flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
A fullish delivery, around off. Lees pushes it to covers this time.
An inside edge this time! On a length, around off. Lees tries to push it towards the off side but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Bowls it fuller and wider outside off. Lees drives it off the bottom of his blade towards point.
Lands it on a length, on off. Lees with a solid block from his crease.
Ngidi starts off with a length delivery, outside off. Lees lets it go.

We are back for the second session of the day! The players have made their way out in the middle. Alex Lees and Joe Root walk out to bat for England. Lungi Ngidi will begin proceedings with the ball. Let's go!
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

England, on the other hand, got three wickets but once again their ploy of bowling too many short deliveries was quite surprising, especially after taking the new ball. Broad eventually decided to go back to his basics of bowling a fullish length with the new ball and got rewarded with two wickets. However, the start with the bat was crucial for England but the out-of-form Zak Crawley played another false shot to make his way back to the pavilion early and the wicket of Pope off the last ball of the session has put England in a hole again. They need something special from hereon and this is a big test now for England and their positive approach, can they put up a fight in the afternoon session? We shall find out. Do join us for the post-Lunch session at 6.10 pm IST (12.40 pm GMT).

South Africa end another session on a high! They have managed to take two wickets quickly again with the ball and this time the spinner Keshav Maharaj has joined the party. What an inspired bowling change this has been by the skipper Dean Elgar and South Africa now lead by 123 runs at Lunch with two English batters back in the hut in their second innings. Earlier in the session, the South African tail just refused to give up easily and added some crucial 37 runs to the overnight score. That took the lead over 160 runs and with the kind of bowling attack South Africa have and the clarity their skipper has shown with his decision-making, England surely have a tough task ahead of them.

OUT! LBW! A wicket for South Africa on the final ball before Lunch! Keshav Maharaj, who did not bowl one over in the first innings, has now picked up two wickets in the second innings. He sends back Ollie Pope now. This is a big, big wicket for South Africa and England are under pressure early in the innings. Coming to the ball - this was a shorter one, it comes in with the arm, on the leg pole. Ollie Pope rocks back and looks to flick this one but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. A loud appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar though decides to review this one. No bat involved there, confirms UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking indicates, three reds. The decision needs to be overturned and Ollie Pope has to depart. A successful review for South Africa. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary.Commentary: Loopy ball, full, around off. Ollie Pope leans forward and defends it out.
Back of a length, around middle and leg, spinning in. Alex Lees flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Tosses this one up, full, around off. Alex Lees blocks it out.
Quicker one, short again, spinning in. Alex Lees defends it out off the back foot.

Dropped! But those chances are always tough! A shorter one, spinning in, around middle and leg. Alex Lees stays in his crease and flicks it towards short leg. The fielder there gets his hands to the ball but fails to hold on to it.
Back of a length, shaping back in this time, around off. Ollie Pope does well to block this one.
Shorter one, outside off, shaping away. Ollie Pope dabs it towards point.
On a length, around middle and leg. Ollie Pope blocks it out.
Another out-swinger, outside off, a length ball. Ollie Pope leaves it alone.
A length ball, nipping back in sharply, around off. Ollie Pope shoulders his arm at this one. The ball hits his thigh pad and goes towards the slip cordon.

FOUR LEG BYES! Kagiso Rabada serves this one down leg, a length ball. Ollie Pope looks to flick this one but he misses. The ball brushes off his pads and goes away from diving fielder towards fine leg for a boundary.
Quicker, turning into the left-hander, around middle. Alex Lees works it away towards mid-wicket.
Keshav Maharaj goes 'round the wicket now, serves a shorter one this time, this one comes in with the angle as well. Ollie Pope stays in his crease and tucks it towards square leg for a single.
Floats it up again, full and around middle. Alex Lees sweeps it towards deep square leg for a single.
Tosses this one up, serves it full and outside off., Alex Lees lunges forward to block this one but he misses and gets hit on his body.
A shorter one now, quicker as well, around middle. Alex Lees skips down the pitch and flicks it to mid-wicket.
A loopy ball, spinning in, outside off. Alex Lees takes a big stride forward and looks to block this but he gets an inside edge back onto his pads.

Nice shot! An overpitched delivery, around off. Alex Lees shows the full face of his blade and drives it down the ground. The ball will not race away to the boundary but the batters pick up three runs.
Outside off, nipping away, a length ball. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Angling in, a length ball, around middle. Ollie Pope works it away towards mid on for a single.
On a length, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope opens the face of his bat and guides it past gully for a brace.
FOUR BYES! Bonus runs for England! A shorter ball, down leg. Ollie Pope leaves it alone. Kyle Verreynne dives but he fails to get there as well. It runs away towards fine leg for a boundary.
Beaten! Good-length delivery, shaping away, outside off. Ollie Pope gets beaten on his outside edge while trying to block this one.

Keshav Maharaj comes 'over the wicket to the left-hander now, serves a shorter one, turning in, around middle and leg. Alex Lees tucks it towards mid-wicket. End of a successful first over from Keshav Maharaj.
Much fuller now, on the pads. Ollie Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. Ollie Pope is off the mark!
Shorter ball, spinning away, around off. Ollie Pope uses the depth of his crease and pushes it towards cover.
Ollie Pope walks out at number 3!

OUT! LBW! Keshav Maharaj strikes in his first over of the game! He gets rid of Zak Crawley and his poor run of form continues. What a move to bring Keshav Maharaj on! He tosses this one up, fuller one, tad slower through the air, on middle. Zak Crawley gets down on his knee and looks to sweep this one but he misses and gets hit on his pad. A loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger without any hesitation. South Africa have got their first wicket.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary.Commentary: Quicker, full, darting it on the pads. Zak Crawley shimmies down the pitch and flicks it towards mid-wicket. Two taken!
Keshav Maharaj comes from 'round the wicket, serves a fuller one, loopy as well, at 87 clicks. Zak Crawley defends it out off the front foot.
Keshav Maharaj is into the attack now. It will be interesting to see how much turn he can extract as Leach got some good turn whenever he bowled.
Swing and a miss! Kagiso Rabada drops it short, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees goes for the pull shot but he fails to get any bat on it.
Another length ball, outside off. Alex Lees punches it off the back foot towards point.
Tighter line now! Around the off pole, a length ball, at 140 clicks. Alex Lees pushes it towards the fielder at mid off.
Width on offer now, full in length. Alex Lees frees his arms and drives it through cover. Two taken.
Shaping away this time, outside off, on a length. Alex Lees offers no shot to that.
On a length from over the wicket, nipping back in. Alex Lees manages to get an inside edge onto his pads while trying to flick this one.
Shaping away, outside off, a length ball. Zak Crawley strides forward and shoulders his arms at it.
This one swings back in, fuller in length, around off, at 143 clicks. Zak Crawley drives and finds the fielder at short cover.
Another good-length delivery, the line is outside off. Zak Crawley leans forward and lets that go through.
Outside off, a length ball. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Fuller ball, swinging in, around middle. Zak Crawley blocks it out towards the leg side.
A good-length ball, on the pads. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but the ball flies over mid-wicket off the leading edge. Anrich Nortje chases the ball and keeps it two runs.
Beaten! Lovely ball! Slightly short again, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees looks to push this away but he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Angling away, shorter one, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Outside off this time, fuller ball. Alex Lees drives it towards the fielder at cover.
Angling in, fuller one, darting it on the pads. Zak Crawley flicks it through square leg for a single.

Another edge! On a length this time, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but the ball goes off the leading edge again once again, away from the fielder at cover this time. Two taken.
Slightly shorter, around middle and leg, extra bounce there as well. Zak Crawley looks to tuck it on the leg side, but the ball goes off the leading edge towards cover.
Fuller ball this time, outside off. Alex Lees blocks it out. Another testing over from Lungi Ngidi comes to an end.

Another ripper from Lungi Ngidi! This is lovely bowling from him. On a length, shaping away a tad, around off. Alex Lees leaves it alone. The ball misses the off pole by a whisker. Tight leave from Alex Lees.
Oh, well bowled! A fuller one this time, jagging back in sharply, around middle and leg. Alex Lees looks to block this one but he manages to get a slight inside edge back onto his pads.
Lungi Ngidi comes 'round the wicket now, serves a length ball, around middle and off. Alex Lees defends it out.
Another ball tailing back in from a good length, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
An in-swinger, a good-length delivery, around middle. Zak Crawley covers the line and blocks the ball.
On a good length and outside off. Lees leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Zak Crawley pushes it to covers for a single.

Ohh...dropped! This is a full delivery, around off. Lees tries to drive it away. However, the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and is travelling straight to Aiden Markram at second slip. Keegan Petersen at third slip dives in front of Aiden Markram and ends up getting one hand to it but the ball does not stick. A single taken as the ball goes behind them.
Beaten! Rabada continues to bowl that length which is just short of good length. It is around off and Lees tries to defend it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
FOUR! Beautifully played! He is off the mark with a boundary. Rabada keeps it tad shorter and around off. Lees gets on top of the bounce and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Rabada lands it on a length, on off. Crawley works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Shorter ball, outside off. Zak Crawley stays in his crease and pushes it off the back foot towards cover for a single. A lovely over Lungi Ngidi! He made the ball talk a lot in his first over.
Pitches it up, much straighter on this occasion, around middle. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
Swinging in, around middle, a length ball. Zak Crawley tucks it towards square leg for a brace. Zak Crawley and England are underway!
Sharp swing there once again! A shorter ball, outside off, swinging in. Zak Crawley leaves it alone. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and makes a lovely stop. Good movement there!
Another on that nips back in, a length ball, around middle. Zak Crawley defends it out.

Lungi Ngidi begins with a length ball, tailing back in, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to flick this one but he misses and gets rapped on his pads. A loud appeal there for LBW, but the umpire says no. Sliding down leg probably.
Lungi Ngidi to share the new ball with Kagiso Rabada.
Another one outside the off pole, a length ball. Alex Lees is happy to let that one go.
A fuller one this time, around middle and off. Alex Lees blocks it out.
Shorter ball, outside off. Alex Lees stays in his crease and looks to cut this away but he gets an under edge back onto the deck.
A length ball, swinging away, outside off. Alex Lees watches it sail through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Alex Lees stays in his crease and blocks it out.
Kagiso Rabada begins with a length ball, shaping away, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
